        THE_MINSTREL_OF_MELODIES_IS_MY_NAME_FOR                                 = 9832,  -- The minstrel of melodies is my name, For a mere # gil I'll recall your past. Your stories of love, anger, triumph, and shame, The river of memories runs deep and vast.
        THE_MINSTREL_OF_MELODIES_IS_MY_NAME_FOR_2                               = 9833,  -- The minstrel of melodies is my name, For a mere # gil I'd recall your past. But I find that you're lacking in cash or in fame, So until that time, my kind offer will last.
        NOW_CLOSE_YOUR_EYES                                                     = 9834,  -- Now close your eyes...
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_PROMATHIA                   = 9835,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. Promathia Missions. Tavnazia Quests 1. Tavnazia Quests 2. Other Quests.
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_AN                          = 9836,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. An Invitation West. The Lost City(pt.1). The Lost City(pt.2). Distant Beliefs. An Eternal Melody(pt.1). An Eternal Melody(pt.2). Sheltering Doubt(pt.1). Sheltering Doubt(pt.2). Sheltering Doubt(pt.3). The Savage. The Secrets of Worship. Slanderous Utterings(pt.1). Slanderous Utterings(pt.2). Southern Legend. Chains and Bonds(pt.1). Chains and Bonds(pt.2). Chains and Bonds(pt.3). The Chains Fall Free.
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_A                           = 9837,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. A Hard Day's Knight(pt.1). A Hard Day's Knight(pt.2). X Marks the Spot(pt.1). X Marks the Spot(pt.2). X Marks the Spot(pt.3). X Marks the Spot(pt.4). X Marks the Spot(pt.5). A Bitter Past(pt.1). A Bitter Past(pt.2). A Bitter Past(pt.3). A Bitter Past(pt.4). A Bitter Past(pt.5). Go! Go! Gobmuffin! Unforgiven(pt.1). Unforgiven(pt.2). Unforgiven(pt.3). Unforgiven(pt.4). The Big One. The Call of the Sea(pt.1). The Call of the Sea(pt.2). The Call of the Sea(pt.3). The Call of the Sea(pt.4). The Call of the Sea(pt.5). Secrets of Ovens Lost. Petals for Parelbriaux(pt.1). Petals for Parelbriaux(pt.2). Petals for Parelbriaux(pt.3). Petals for Parelbriaux(pt.4). Elderly Pursuits(pt.1). Elderly Pursuits(pt.2).
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_BEHIND                      = 9838,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. Behind the Smile(pt.1). Behind the Smile(pt.2). Forbidden Doors(pt.1). Forbidden Doors(pt.2). In Search of the Truth(pt.1). In Search of the Truth(pt.2). In Search of the Truth(pt.3). In Search of the Truth(pt.4). In Search of the Truth(pt.5). In Search of the Truth(pt.6). In Search of the Truth(pt.7). In Search of the Truth(pt.8). In Search of the Truth(pt.9). In Search of the Truth(pt.10). In Search of the Truth(pt.11). In Search of the Truth(pt.12). In Search of the Truth(pt.13). Uninvited Guests. Tango with a Tracker.
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_THE                         = 9839,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. The Search for Goldmane. Dynamis - The Shrouded Land. Dynamis Interloper(pt.1). Dynamis Interloper(pt.2). Dynamis Interloper(pt.3). Dynamis Interloper(pt.4). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.1). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.2). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.3). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.4). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.5). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.6). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.7). VW Op. #026: Tavnazian Terrors(pt.8). Trust (Prishe).
        YOU_I_THOUGHT_YOU_HAD_PERISHED                                          = 9840,  -- You... I thought you had perished!
        HMPH_I_SEE_THE_BOY_IS_NOT_WITH                                          = 9841,  -- Hmph. I see the boy is not with you...
        VERY_WELL_LET_US_PUT_OUR_DIFFERENCES_ASIDE                              = 9842,  -- Very well. Let us put our differences aside for the moment. However, I suggest that you do not make any sudden movements, as we are being watched...
        TRAVELERS_THIS_PLACE_IS_NOTHING_BUT_A_MEMORY                            = 9843,  -- Travelers. This place is nothing but a memory fleeting on the edge of time. There is little we have to offer outsiders.
        AND_SO_I_MUST_ASK_OF_YOU_THESE                                          = 9844,  -- And so I must ask of you these questions: From where have you come, and to where do you go? If your conscience is clean and your intentions just, you should have no reason not to provide me with answers.
        YEAH_PROVE_THAT_YOU_RE_INNOCENT                                         = 9845,  -- Yeah! Prove that you're innocent!
        YEAH_A_FIGHT_TO_THE_DEATH                                               = 9846,  -- Yeah! A fight to the death!
        WHAT_YOU_SAY_THAT_THESE_TARUTARU_STOLE_SOMETHING                        = 9847,  -- What, you say that these Tarutaru stole something from you?
        BUT_THAT_WAS                                                            = 9848,  -- But that was...
        OW_OW_OUCH                                                              = 9849,  -- Ow-ow-ouch!
        STEALING_ITEMS_FROM_AN_UNCONSCIOUS_STRANGER_WHAT_WERE                   = 9850,  -- Stealing items from an unconscious stranger! What were you three thinking!?
        BUT_THAT_AMULET_IS_PRISHE_S_I_BET                                       = 9851,  -- But that amulet is Prishe's! I bet that funny-looking adventurer stole it from her!
        IT_DOES_CLOSELY_RESEMBLE_THE_ONE_PRISHE_HAD                             = 9852,  -- It does closely resemble the one Prishe had in her possession...
        AMULET_SO_THAT_EXPLAINS                                                 = 9853,  -- Amulet!? So that explains...
        WE_SHALL_WAIT_FOR_PRISHE_S_RETURN_SHE                                   = 9854,  -- We shall wait for Prishe's return. She will know whether the amulet is hers or not. Until that time, I suggest that you rest here in the safehold.
        HOWEVER_REMEMBER_THAT_YOU_ARE_NOT_WELCOME_AND                           = 9855,  -- However, remember that you are not welcome, and the moment the issue at hand is solved, you will be asked to leave and never come back.
        WELCOME_TO_OUR_HUMBLE_CITY_THOUGH_THERE_IS                              = 9856,  -- Welcome to our humble city, though there is little left of it... I heard from Justinius the details of your predicament.
        HE_MENTIONED_THAT_YOU_WERE_FROM_THE_MAINLAND                            = 9857,  -- He mentioned that you were from the mainland.
        TELL_ME_WHAT_IS_THE_SITUATION_BEYOND_THE                                = 9858,  -- Tell me, what is the situation beyond the churning seas?
        I_SEE_THE_STRUGGLE_FOR_PEACE_CONTINUES                                  = 9859,  -- I see... [The lord of the beastmen has returned and/Even after the Shadow Lord's defeat,] the struggle for peace continues.
        NO_ONE_HAS_THE_TIME_TO_WONDER_ABOUT                                     = 9860,  -- No one has the time to wonder about the fates of their lost brothers...
        THIS_IS_TAVNAZIA_A_NEW_TAVNAZIA_BUILT_FROM                              = 9861,  -- This is Tavnazia... A new Tavnazia, built from the ruins of the once mighty Marquisate. For twenty years, the survivors of the Great War toiled to create what you see here.
        FOR_TWENTY_YEARS_WE_HAVE_DUG_AND_CARVED                                 = 9862,  -- For twenty years, we have dug and carved our way up from a narrow storageway below the Tavnazian Cathedral...
        AS_AN_ADVENTURER_I_AM_SURE_YOU_HAVE                                     = 9863,  -- As an adventurer, I am sure you have heard tales of the Pearl of Zafmlug--the renowned Tavnazian Marquisate.
        HER_WIDE_HARBORS_WOULD_WELCOME_SHIPS_FROM_ALL                           = 9864,  -- Her wide harbors would welcome ships from all corners of Vana'diel, carrying never-before-seen goods and treasures.
        A_MECCA_OF_TRADE_A_PLACE_WHERE_DREAMS                                   = 9865,  -- A mecca of trade. A place where dreams of wealth and success could become reality... It was the golden age of Tavnazia.
        BUT_IT_ALL_CAME_TO_A_CLOSE_TWENTY                                       = 9866,  -- But it all came to a close twenty years ago. The beastman hordes concentrated their attack on our fair nation, and when they were through, there was nothing left but a wasteland uninhabitable by even the foulest of creatures.
        WE_TOO_SHOULD_HAVE_MET_THE_SAME_FATE                                    = 9867,  -- We, too, should have met the same fate as the Marquisate...
        LATE_IN_OUR_ESCAPE_FROM_THE_PENINSULA_WE                                = 9868,  -- Late in our escape from the peninsula, we made for the cathedral, where we awaited our deaths at the hands of the Orcs.
        HOWEVER_IT_WAS_NOT_THE_ORCS_WHO_ARRIVED                                 = 9869,  -- However, it was not the Orcs who arrived, but the cardinal, Mildaurion C Giloumet.
        SHE_TENDED_TO_OUR_WOUNDED_BODIES_AND_SPIRITS                            = 9870,  -- She tended to our wounded bodies and spirits, and informed us how to escape.
        SHE_OPENED_THE_GATES_TO_THE_LOWER_PARTS                                 = 9871,  -- She opened the gates to the lower parts of the cathedral, and told us to follow the delivery tunnels to the city.
        WE_DID_AS_WE_WERE_TOLD_AND_IT                                           = 9872,  -- We did as we were told, and it was not long before we arrived at the subterranean harbor deep beneath this place.
        HOWEVER_BY_THE_TIME_WE_HAD_ARRIVED_THE                                  = 9873,  -- However, by the time we had arrived, the boats had already gone, and a terrible explosion had destroyed the landbridge to Quon... We were trapped...
        BUT_EVEN_WITH_OUR_BACKS_AGAINST_THE_WALL                                = 9874,  -- But even with our backs against the wall of despair, the courage and faith we had received from the cardinal remained in our hearts.
        FOR_THE_PAST_TWENTY_YEARS_WE_HAVE_SURVIVED                              = 9875,  -- For the past twenty years we have survived on the belief that Altana will save us. It is that belief that has helped us to come together and rebuild our nation.
        HOWEVER_WE_STILL_STRUGGLE_TO_PROVIDE_FOR_EVEN                           = 9876,  -- However, we still struggle to provide for even ourselves. I am sorry we cannot offer you any more than a warm welcome.
        BUT_PLEASE_FEEL_FREE_TO_UTILIZE_ANY_OF                                  = 9877,  -- But please, feel free to utilize any of our facilities.
        I_PRAY_THAT_THE_POWERS_THAT_LED_YOU                                     = 9878,  -- I pray that the powers that led you to Tavnazia become a blessing for both our peoples.
        I_REALIZE_THAT_BACK_ON_THE_MAINLAND_NO                                  = 9879,  -- I realize that back on the mainland, no one has the time to wonder about the fates of their lost brothers.
        HOWEVER_I_PRAY_THAT_THE_POWERS_THAT_LED                                 = 9880,  -- However, I pray that the powers that led you to Tavnazia turn out to be a blessing for both our peoples.
