        MISS_MILDAURION_YOU_VE_GOT_TO_BE_KIDDING                                = 10198,  -- Miss Mildaurion! You've got to be kidding!?
        I_KNOW_NEITHER_OF_HER_GUILT_NOR_INNOCENCE                               = 10199,  -- I know neither of her guilt nor innocence, and that is why I have been searching for anyone who remembers her. It looks as if I finally found someone who can give me some useful information.
        LET_ME_TAKE_THE_GIRL_I_CAN_SEE                                          = 10200,  -- Let me take the girl. I can see that her presence has been quite the burden on you and your people.
        WELL_IF_THIS_IS_WHAT_THE_CATHEDRAL_DESIRES                              = 10201,  -- Well... If this is what the cathedral desires, I am not one to stand in its way...
        GRANPERE_2                                                              = 10202,  -- Granpere!
        ULMIA_DON_T_WORRY_I_WAS_BEGINNING_TO                                    = 10203,  -- Ulmia, don't worry. I was beginning to think that it's about time everybody learned the truth.
        I_VE_GOTTA_DO_SOMETHING_OR_PEOPLE_WILL                                  = 10204,  -- I've gotta do something, or people will continue to doubt and hate me.
        PRISHE_BUT                                                              = 10205,  -- Prishe... But...!
        HEY_LOUVERANCE_AS_MUCH_AS_I_D_LIKE                                      = 10206,  -- Hey, Louverance! As much as I'd like to take up your offer of a free cruise to the Kingdom, I'm gonna have to pass. I gotta go to the Northlands with these guys before I can do anything else.
        LIKE_THEY_SAY_A_PROMISE_IS_A_PROMISE                                    = 10207,  -- Like they say, a promise is a promise.
        YES_WE_MUST_HURRY_TO_THE_NORTHLANDS_TO                                  = 10208,  -- Yes! We must hurry to the Northlands to assist the Jeunoan diplomat, Nag'molada.
        THE_FUTURE_OF_VANA_DIEL_RIDES_ON_THIS                                   = 10209,  -- The future of Vana'diel rides on this crucial mission. I understand your orders, Sir Louverance, but there are more important issues we must first address.
        YOU_ARE_WORKING_WITH_NAG_MOLADA_I_SEE                                   = 10210,  -- You are working with Nag'molada...? I see...
        I_OFFER_YOU_THIS_SUGGESTION                                             = 10211,  -- I offer you this suggestion...
        COME_TO_MY_AIRSHIP_AND_TELL_ME_WHAT                                     = 10212,  -- Come to my airship and tell me what you know of Cardinal Mildaurion.
        WHEN_YOU_HAVE_ANSWERED_ALL_MY_QUESTIONS_I                               = 10213,  -- When you have answered all my questions, I shall personally fly you to the Northlands.
        CAN_I_ASSUME_THAT_I_TOO_AM_WELCOME                                      = 10214,  -- Can I assume that I, too, am welcome aboard your ship?
        AS_A_MESSENGER_FROM_THE_EASTERN_DYNASTY_I                               = 10215,  -- As a messenger from the Eastern dynasty, I request an audience with the royaulis.
        UNDERSTOOD_I_WILL_BE_WAITING_AT_THE_SEALION                             = 10216,  -- Understood. I will be waiting at the Sealion's Den.
        LADY_PRISHE_I_AM_PLEASED_TO_FIND_OUT                                    = 10217,  -- Lady Prishe, I am pleased to find out that you are a woman of understanding. Now make your goodbyes and hurry to the docks.
        I_WAS_RELIEVED_TO_HEAR_THAT_SIR_LOUVERANCE                              = 10218,  -- I was relieved to hear that Sir Louverance would be taking Prishe into his custody.
        SHE_WILL_BE_BETTER_OFF_WITH_THE_SAN                                     = 10219,  -- She will be better off with the San d'Orian Cathedral seeing to her needs.
        HOWEVER_I_NEVER_IMAGINED_THAT_CARDINAL_MILDAURION_WAS                   = 10220,  -- However, I never imagined that Cardinal Mildaurion was capable of committing crimes against the Kingdom.
        TO_THINK_THAT_SUCH_A_NOBLE_WOMAN_COULD                                  = 10221,  -- To think that such a noble woman could resort to criminal activity... The heart is a mysterious thing. It can often change without even a hint of notice.
        SO_ULMIA_TRULY_LEFT_WITH_PRISHE                                         = 10222,  -- So Ulmia truly left with Prishe...
        PERHAPS_THERE_WAS_NOTHING_THAT_AN_OLD_MAN                               = 10223,  -- Perhaps there was nothing that an old man such as myself could have done to prevent it...
        I_WILL_NOT_ALLOW_YOU_TO_GO_TAGGING                                      = 10224,  -- I will not allow you to go tagging along with the abhorrent one! I will not allow it!
        GRANPERE_YOU_KNOW_AS_WELL_AS_I_DO                                       = 10225,  -- Granpere, you know as well as I do...
        THERE_IS_NOTHING_ABHORRENT_ABOUT_PRISHE                                 = 10226,  -- There is nothing abhorrent about Prishe...
        AND_I_CAN_NO_LONGER_IGNORE_THE_PROBLEMS                                 = 10227,  -- And I can no longer ignore the problems that loom before us. Goodbye, Granpere.
        ULMIA                                                                   = 10228,  -- Ulmia!
        I_DID_EVERYTHING_I_COULD_TO_PROVIDE_FOR                                 = 10229,  -- I did everything I could to provide for my friends and family in this cursed place...
        I_NEVER_REALIZED_THAT_MY_ACTIONS_WERE_ONLY                              = 10230,  -- I never realized that my actions were only tying them down...
        IS_ULMIA_HOW_IS_SHE_DOING                                               = 10231,  -- %... Is Ulmia... How is she doing?
        GREETINGS_DESPACHIAIRE_IT_HAS_BEEN_TOO_LONG                             = 10232,  -- Greetings, Despachiaire. It has been too long.
        SIR_LOUVERANCE                                                          = 10233,  -- Sir Louverance!
        YOU_NEED_NOT_WORRY_SHE_IS_FINE_AND                                      = 10234,  -- You need not worry. She is fine. % and I travel the world in search of a truth--a single truth that will restore light to Vana'diel and her children.
        YOUR_GRANDDAUGHTER_EMBRACES_THE_SAME_GOAL_AS_WE                         = 10235,  -- Your granddaughter embraces the same goal as we do, and she will not give up until she has reached it.
        I_CAN_SLEEP_EASIER_KNOWING_THAT_SUCH_A                                  = 10236,  -- I can sleep easier knowing that such a noble knight as yourself is watching over my dear Ulmia. However, she is often one to hide her true feelings away from others, even though she may be in pain.
        YOU_YOU_ARE_NOT_CAUSING_HER_ANY_PAIN                                    = 10237,  -- You... You are not causing her any pain, are you?
        ULMIA_IS_A_VERY_STRONG_WILLED_YOUNG_WOMAN                               = 10238,  -- Ulmia is a very strong-willed young woman. She understands the responsibilities that lie before her and will not cower before them.
        THAT_IS_WHY_SHE_BLAMED_HERSELF_FOR_NOT                                  = 10239,  -- That is why she blamed herself for not knowing more about the painting of Al'Taieu kept in the Tavnazian Cathedral's reliquiarium.
        WH_WHAT                                                                 = 10240,  -- Wh-what!?
        LADY_ULMIA_IS_NOT_A_THEOLOGIAN_OF_THE                                   = 10241,  -- Lady Ulmia is not a theologian of the cathedral. No one expects her to know of the painting. However...
        EXACTLY_THERE_IS_NO_WAY_SHE_COULD_KNOW                                  = 10242,  -- Exactly! There is no way she could know of the painting. She was only a mere child when the piece was donated to the cathedral. Oh, why must you blame yourself, poor Ulmia?
        SIR_LOUVERANCE_I_KNOW_SOME_OF_THE_HISTORY                               = 10243,  -- Sir Louverance! I know some of the history behind the painting. Let me tell you of what I know.
        LONG_AGO_I_HELPED_IN_THE_TRANSPORT_OF                                   = 10244,  -- Long ago, I helped in the transport of the relic to the cathedral. Much tumult arose as a result of bringing that painting here.
        YOUR_ASSISTANCE_IS_GREATLY_APPRECIATED_DESPACHIAIRE_I_WILL              = 10245,  -- Your assistance is greatly appreciated, Despachiaire. I will relay everything you tell me to your granddaughter.
        YES_IT_WAS_SOME_TWENTY_FIVE_YEARS_AGO                                   = 10246,  -- Yes... It was some twenty-five years ago that the painting was brought to the archipelago.
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_MARQUISATE_OFFICIALS_THE_PAINTING_WAS                  = 10247,  -- According to the Marquisate officials, the painting was found deep within ancient ruins known as the Temple of Uggalepih.
        IT_IS_SAID_THAT_THE_PAINTING_DEPICTS_A                                  = 10248,  -- It is said that the painting depicts a scene in the verse of a legendary song--the ancients and their attempt to open the Gates of Paradise...
        YES_I_REMEMBER_IT_LIKE_IT_WAS_YESTERDAY                                 = 10249,  -- Yes, I remember it like it was yesterday... A gate of light hovering over a grand city... The gatekeeper roaring to the heavens...
        THE_GATEKEEPER_TOOK_THE_SHAPE_OF_A_MIGHTY                               = 10250,  -- The gatekeeper took the shape of a mighty dragon. However, his four legs were bound by mighty shackles.
        THIS_IMAGE_WAS_THE_STRONGEST_IN_THE_PAINTING                            = 10251,  -- This image was the strongest in the painting. Many of the missionaries that came to view the painting would often call it the relic of chains, or the relic of the dragon.
        I_SEE_SO_AT_THAT_TIME_THE_IDENTITY                                      = 10252,  -- I see... So at that time the identity of the city was still unknown...
        YES_UNTIL_CARDINAL_MILDAURION_VIEWED_THE_PAINTING_IT                    = 10253,  -- Yes, until Cardinal Mildaurion viewed the painting. It was she who told us the city was Al'Taieu.
        AS_PUNISHMENT_FOR_DEFYING_THE_GODS_THE_CITY                             = 10254,  -- As punishment for defying the gods, the city of Al'Taieu was destroyed and banished to the bottom of the northern sea. After the cardinal revealed the truth of the painting, many a canticle was sung of this legend. There wasn't a soul in Tavnazia who had not heard one while sipping down a glass of brew in the local pub.
        HOWEVER_WHY_DID_THE_CARDINAL_KNOW_OF_THE                                = 10255,  -- However... Why did the cardinal know of the city and its legend?
        THOUGH_I_MAY_BE_MISTAKEN_I_SEEM_TO                                      = 10256,  -- Though I may be mistaken, I seem to recall that before arriving in Tavnazia, Mildaurion was a priest who wandered the Outlands on a quest for spiritual enlightenment.
        I_HAVE_ALSO_HEARD_TALES_THAT_MANY_OF                                    = 10257,  -- I have also heard tales that many of the holy relics that reached the archipelago were brought from the Outlands by thieves and pirates. Perhaps the cardinal obtained her knowledge of Al'Taieu in these forsaken areas.
        THE_OUTLANDS_I_SEE                                                      = 10258,  -- The Outlands... I see...
        YES_I_ALSO_REMEMBER_HOW_A_GROUP_OF                                      = 10259,  -- Yes, I also remember how a group of Mithra came from those Outlands, demanding that we return the painting to the temple.
        I_TOO_HAVE_HEARD_THAT_TALE_AFTER_A                                      = 10260,  -- I, too, have heard that tale. After a long series of talks, the cardinal was able to convince the Mithra to allow the painting to remain in Tavnazia, without defacing the honor of the cathedral.
        WE_WERE_RELIEVED_AND_WITH_THOSE_MITHRA_BEASTS                           = 10261,  -- We were relieved, and with those Mithra beasts gone, we could go back to our normal, everyday lives.
        MITHRA_PERHAPS_THEY_KNOW_MORE_OF_THE_PAINTING                           = 10262,  -- Mithra... Perhaps they know more of the painting...
        DESPACHIAIRE_WOULD_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_RECALL_THE_NAMES                       = 10263,  -- Despachiaire, would you happen to recall the names of the Mithra or where exactly they came from?
        I_DO_NOT_REMEMBER_THEIR_NAMES_I_DO                                      = 10264,  -- I do not remember their names. I do not think they were ever referred to by anything other than the title of sin hunters.
        SIN_HUNTERS_ASSASSINS_SENT_FROM_THE_MITHRAN_HOMELAND                    = 10265,  -- Sin hunters. Assassins sent from the Mithran homeland to do the dirty work of the Grand Chieftainness...
        SO_THIS_PAINTING_MUST_BE_OF_GREAT_IMPORTANCE                            = 10266,  -- So this painting must be of great importance to their race...
        SIR_LOUVERANCE_A_YOUNG_MITHRAN_SIN_HUNTER_VISITED                       = 10267,  -- Sir Louverance. A young Mithran sin hunter visited the safehold a number of days ago.
        IF_YOU_CAN_FIND_HER_SHE_MAY_BE                                          = 10268,  -- If you can find her, she may be able to better inform you of the secrets behind the painting.
        A_SIN_HUNTER_WAS_HERE                                                   = 10269,  -- A sin hunter...was here!?
        EXCELLENT_DESPACHIAIRE_I_THANK_YOU_VERY_MUCH_FOR                        = 10270,  -- Excellent... Despachiaire, I thank you very much for your assistance. I will heed your advice and begin a search for this Mithra.
        A_SIN_HUNTER_IN_TAVNAZIA_A_QUITE_UNEXPECTED                             = 10271,  -- A sin hunter in Tavnazia... A quite unexpected turn of events, wouldn't you say, %?
        LET_US_TRAVEL_TO_WINDURST_AND_INQUIRE_WITH                              = 10272,  -- Let us travel to Windurst and inquire with the chieftainness about the sin hunters and the painting they desire.
        A_YOUNG_MITHRAN_SIN_HUNTER_VISITED_THE_SAFEHOLD                         = 10273,  -- A young Mithran sin hunter visited the safehold a number of days ago. She said she was searching for Prishe.
        IF_YOU_CAN_FIND_HER_PERHAPS_SHE_MAY                                     = 10274,  -- If you can find her, perhaps she may be able to better inform you of the secrets behind the painting.
        AS_YOU_KNOW_A_YOUNG_MITHRAN_SIN_HUNTER                                  = 10275,  -- As you know, a young Mithran sin hunter visited the safehold a number of days ago.
        I_CANNOT_IMAGINE_FOR_WHAT_REASONS_SHE_VISITED                           = 10276,  -- I cannot imagine for what reasons she visited us. However, if you can find her, she may be able to better inform you of the secrets behind the painting.
