        WHY_WHAT_A_KIND_GESTURE_I_AM_VERY                                       = 10716,  -- Why, what a kind gesture. I am very proud of you.
        YOU_ARE_HEH_HEH_HEAR_THAT_LEPORAITCEAU_SHE                              = 10717,  -- You are? Heh heh. Hear that, Leporaitceau? She's proud of me! Me, not you!
        WHEN_I_GROW_UP_I_M_GOING_TO_2                                           = 10718,  -- When I grow up, I'm going to be a super adventurer, just like my new best friend!
        LATELY_I_SPEND_MY_DAYS_REMINISCING_OF_THE                               = 10719,  -- Lately I spend my days reminiscing of the past... Ah, how beautiful the Marquisate was... If I could only take you there...
        RECENTLY_THE_LIGHT_THAT_SHINES_DOWN_ON_THE                              = 10720,  -- Recently, the light that shines down on the safehold seems brighter than it has been in ages. <Sigh> I wonder if Tavnazia will ever regain the glory of old...
        THERE_S_NOTHING_TO_DO_IN_THIS_MUSTY                                     = 10721,  -- There's nothing to do in this musty old cave. I wanna go outside and play in the meadows!
        I_VE_HEARD_LOTS_OF_NEAT_STORIES_FROM                                    = 10722,  -- I've heard lots of neat stories from all the adventurers visiting the safehold. I can't wait until I'm old enough to ditch this smelly cave and go someplace exciting!
        I_WILL_NOT_REST_UNTIL_THE_MARQUISATE_HAS                                = 10723,  -- I will not rest until the Marquisate has become as grand and as powerful as it was before the Great War!
        WITH_THE_ARRIVAL_OF_THE_AIRSHIPS_THE_SITUATION                          = 10724,  -- With the arrival of the airships, the situation in Tavnazia has begun to take a turn for the better.
        ONCE_AGAIN_VANA_DIEL_WILL_HEAR_THE_ROAR                                 = 10725,  -- Once again Vana'diel will hear the roar of the mighty sealion!
        SIGH_I_WONDER_IF_I_LL_EVER_HAVE                                         = 10726,  -- <Sigh> I wonder if I'll ever have the chance to catch the big one before I cross that final river to Paradise...
        LADDIE_LASSIE_HAVE_YOU_EVER_DREAMED_OF_REELING                          = 10727,  -- Laddie/Lassie], have you ever dreamed of reeling in the impossible? Hooking the beast that legends are made of?
        FISH_IN_YOUR_EYES_ALL_THE_TIME_I                                        = 10728,  -- Fish in your eyes? All the time! I'm a vegetarian.
        VEGETARIAN_I_DON_T_HAVE_ANY_BUSINESS_WITH                               = 10729,  -- Vegetarian!? I don't have any business with you leaf-eaters! Move along!
        NOT_BUT_A_FEW_DAYS_AGO_A_YOUNG                                          = 10730,  -- Not but a few days ago, a young adventurer stopped by the safehold saying that she spotted an enormous something swimming in the waters of Lufaise Meadows. She mentioned that she tried to fish the beast up, but was unsuccessful. Just hearing that fish tale started my blood a-boiling.
        I_DON_T_MEAN_TO_BLOW_MY_OWN                                             = 10731,  -- I don't mean to blow my own horn, but when I was still a young 'un, there wasn't a soul in Tavnazia that didn't know the name Trawlin' Travonce. I was the finest fisherman on the whole peninsula.
        AND_I_STILL_AM_BUT_MY_SKILLS_WITH                                       = 10732,  -- And I still am, but my skills with the sword have dropped off a wee bit in these past few years.
        WITH_ALL_THE_CRAZED_BEASTMEN_ROAMING_THE_ISLANDS                        = 10733,  -- With all the crazed beastmen roaming the islands and the savage monsters lurking below the waters, an old man can no longer just sit back and enjoy a day casting his line on the emerald waters of Tavnazia.
        NOW_IF_SOME_NICE_STRONG_YOUNG_ADVENTURER_WOULD                          = 10734,  -- Now, if some nice strong young adventurer would come out with me and take care of all the pests while I fished, good ol' Trawlin' Travonce could snatch up the big one in the blink of an eye, give or take a few blinks.
        TRAVONCE_LOOKS_AT_YOU_WITH_PUPPY_DOG_EYES                               = 10735,  -- Travonce looks at you with puppy-dog eyes.
        SIGH_ISN_T_THERE_ANYONE_OUT_THERE_ANYONE                                = 10736,  -- <Sigh> Isn't there anyone out there...? Anyone at all...?
        WILL_NO_ONE_GRANT_AN_OLD_MAN_HIS                                        = 10737,  -- Will no one grant an old man his final wish before he withers away and dies...alone...and fishless?
        HELP_HIM_REALIZE_HIS_DREAM_HOW_COULD_YOU                                = 10738,  -- Help him realize his dream? How could you say no? How could you say yes?
        YOU_LL_HELP_ME_WHAT_A_KIND_YOUNG                                        = 10739,  -- You'll help me!? What a kind young child you are! I'll go gather my equipment. You know what they say, an unprepared fisherman is a...a...
        ANYWAY_YOU_D_BETTER_GO_MAKE_YOUR_PREPARATIONS                           = 10740,  -- Anyway, you'd better go make your preparations as well. When you're ready, I'll be waiting at the Porte d'Altendise. What, you don't know where that is? There are four exits in the northern end of the safehold, right? Porte d'Altendise is the southeastern one.
        OH_AND_I_LIKE_TO_SLEEP_IN_SO                                            = 10741,  -- Oh, and I like to sleep in, so don't show up until after lunchtime. But don't come too late. We have to find that fish before he swims off somewhere to sleep.
        YOUNG_ADVENTURERS_THESE_DAYS_NO_RESPECT_FOR_THEIR                       = 10742,  -- Young adventurers these days... No respect for their elders. And to top that off, they're all nothing but a lot of spineless jellyfish, to boot!
        AND_SO_THE_BIG_ONE_GOT_AWAY_AGAIN                                       = 10743,  -- And so the big one got away again... Maybe I am getting too old for this...
        AH_THAT_S_RIGHT_I_GUESS_I_SHOULD                                        = 10744,  -- Ah, that's right. I guess I should give you something in return for helping me out. How about this fishing gear? It doesn't look like an old, washed-up geezer like me will be needing it any more...
        AT_LEAST_I_HAD_THE_OPPORTUNITY_TO_GO                                    = 10745,  -- At least I had the opportunity to go out under the crisp, clean Tavnazian sky one last time before I die... <Sigh>...
        THE_OTHER_DAY_A_FINE_YOUNG_MAN_LADY                                     = 10746,  -- The other day, a fine young man/lady] helped me go out in search of the big one. Come to think of it, he/she] looked an awful lot like you...
        WHY_YOU_LOOK_LIKE_AN_ENERGETIC_LAD_LASS                                 = 10747,  -- Why, you look like an energetic lad/lass], all chock full o' pep. If I could only find myself someone like you to help an old man fulfill his final wish...
        DON_T_TELL_ME_THAT_YOU_RE_HAVING                                        = 10748,  -- Don't tell me that you're having second thoughts. <Sigh> Maybe it's time I just went somewhere to crawl up and die...
        LEAVE_HIM_TO_CRAWL_UP_AND_DIE_WHY                                       = 10749,  -- Leave him to crawl up and die? Why not? Not just yet.
        THIS_SAFEHOLD_WE_ALL_LIVE_IN_NOW_WAS                                    = 10750,  -- This safehold we all live in now was once part of the Tavnazian Cathedral, as were the Sealion's Den and the Sacrarium.
        AID_FROM_JEUNO_HAS_BEGUN_ARRIVING_IN_OUR                                = 10751,  -- Aid from Jeuno has begun arriving in our city. While these items may improve our ways of life at the moment, many of us still worry about the future of the safehold.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_JOURNEYED_TO_THE_SACRARIUM                                = 10752,  -- Have you ever journeyed to the Sacrarium?
        SINCE_I_WAS_A_CHILD_IT_HAS_BEEN                                         = 10753,  -- Since I was a child, it has been my dream to become an architect. I often walk alone to the Sacrarium's libraries to study the books on ancient architecture.
        ONE_DAY_WHILE_READING_A_VOLUME_ON_TAVNAZIAN                             = 10754,  -- One day, while reading a volume on Tavnazian masonry, I discovered a tattered old set of floorplans.
        HOWEVER_DUE_TO_ITS_CONDITION_THERE_WERE_MANY                            = 10755,  -- However, due to its condition, there were many sections of it that were difficult to make out. If we could find another copy, I might be able to construct a new map of the Sacrarium based on the combined sets of plans.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_COME_ACROSS_EVEN_A                                     = 10756,  -- If you happen to come across even a fragment of a document that may be of use, bring it back to me and I will do my best to piece together the puzzle.
        ID_10757                                                                = 10757,  -- %!
        YES_THIS_LOOKS_SIMILAR_TO_THE_SET_OF                                    = 10758,  -- Yes, this looks similar to the set of plans I found before... But it, too, is damaged terribly. I cannot tell exactly which part of the Sacrarium it describes.
        HM_YOU_SAY_YOU_FOUND_THIS_DOCUMENT_IN                                   = 10759,  -- Hm? You say you found this document in a treasure chest?
        DO_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_REMEMBER_IN_WHAT_AREA                                  = 10760,  -- Do you happen to remember in what area of the Sacrarium the chest was located?
        THERE_IS_A_GOOD_CHANCE_THAT_THE_PLANS                                   = 10761,  -- There is a good chance that the plans describe the same area.
        WHERE_DID_YOU_FIND_THE_CHEST_THINK_A                                    = 10762,  -- Where did you find the chest? Think a little longer. Around <F-5>. Around <G-5>. Around <H-5>. Around <F-11>. Around <G-11>. Around <H-11>.
        WHERE_DID_YOU_FIND_THE_CHEST_THINK_A_2                                  = 10763,  -- Where did you find the chest? Think a little longer. Around <F-7>. Around <G-7>. Around <H-7>. Around <F-9>. Around <G-9>. Around <H-9>.
        WHERE_DID_YOU_FIND_THE_CHEST_THINK_A_3                                  = 10764,  -- Where did you find the chest? Think a little longer. Around <I-6>. Around <J-6>. Around <K-7>. Around <K-9>. Around <I-10>. Around <J-10>.
        WHERE_DID_YOU_FIND_THE_CHEST_THINK_A_4                                  = 10765,  -- Where did you find the chest? Think a little longer. Around <J-7>. Around <K-7>. Around <I-8>. Around <L-8>. Around <J-9>. Around <K-9>.
        I_SEE_I_WILL_USE_THAT_INFORMATION_TO                                    = 10766,  -- I see... I will use that information to attempt to reconstruct a precise map of the area. It will take me about a day to complete my work. Please come back tomorrow.
        IT_WILL_TAKE_ME_ABOUT_A_DAY_TO                                          = 10767,  -- It will take me about a day to complete my work on the map of the Sacrarium. Please come back tomorrow.
        I_APOLOGIZE_THE_INFORMATION_YOU_PROVIDED_WAS_NOT                        = 10768,  -- I apologize. The information you provided was not precise enough for me to finish the map.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_COME_ACROSS_ANY_MORE                                   = 10769,  -- If you happen to come across any more pieces of the Sacrarium floorplans, please bring them to me. I will not give up until I've created a perfect map!
        I_SUCCEEDED_IN_COMPLETING_THE                                           = 10770,  -- %! I succeeded in completing the %!
        I_NEVER_IMAGINED_THAT_THE_AREA_COULD_BE                                 = 10771,  -- I never imagined that the area could be so simple, yet complicated...
        THIS_HAS_BEEN_A_WONDERFUL_EXPERIENCE_FOR_ME                             = 10772,  -- This has been a wonderful experience for me. I have learned so much about the architecture of the cathedral.
        FEEL_FREE_TO_TAKE_THE_MAP_WITH_YOU                                      = 10773,  -- Feel free to take the map with you. I have already made myself a copy. It is the least I can do.
        I_SHALL_MAKE_SURE_TO_PRESERVE_IT_WITH                                   = 10774,  -- I shall make sure to preserve it with the care due the most precious of research materials.
        WOULD_YOU_TAKE_A_LOOK_AT_THOSE_FUZZY                                    = 10775,  -- Would you take a look at those fuzzy guys over there? Can you believe that they'd come all the way from their cozy homes in Moogle-land to a town in the middle of nowhere? They must be really crazy or really bored.
        NOW_THAT_THE_AIRSHIPS_FROM_JEUNO_HAVE_STARTED                           = 10776,  -- Now that the airships from Jeuno have started arriving, there are a lot more people passing through the safehold. Those fuzzy guys over there seem pretty happy considering all the extra work.
        YOU_KNOW_ABOUT_WHAT_HAPPENED_TO_CAPE_RIVERNE                            = 10777,  -- You know about what happened to Cape Riverne, right?
        WELL_DID_YOU_KNOW_THAT_THERE_S_THIS                                     = 10778,  -- Well, did you know that there's this traveling Goblin that's trying to make a new map of the area? Bet you didn't!
        AND_I_ALSO_BET_YOU_DIDN_T_KNOW                                          = 10779,  -- And I also bet you didn't know it was that Goblin who gave the areas their strange names--Site #A01 and Site #B01. Yeah, I just met the cute little girl a couple of days ago. She came to the safehold wanting to buy some supplies for her journey.
        SHE_SAID_THAT_SHE_WAS_ALMOST_DONE_WITH                                  = 10780,  -- She said that she was almost done with the map, but still hadn't finished trekking through the most dangerous part of the area.
        NOW_THAT_I_THINK_OF_IT_THERE_S                                          = 10781,  -- Now that I think of it, there's no way that sweet Gobmuffin can possibly make it on her own... Hey, you're a strong-looking adventurer. Would you go to Cape Riverne and see if you can find her and bring her back? It's a matter of life or death!
        WOULD_YOU_GO_TO_CAPE_RIVERNE_AND_SEE                                    = 10782,  -- Would you go to Cape Riverne and see if you can find that sweet Gobmuffin and bring her back? It's a matter of life or death!
        HUH_YOU_WERE_ATTACKED_BY_WHAT_A_STRANGE                                 = 10783,  -- Huh!? You were attacked by what!? A strange pack of Moblins!? What's a Moblin?
        AH_3                                                                    = 10784,  -- Ah...
        SWIKASTOQQ_IS_MOBLINN_SWIKASTOQQ_WENTT_TO_CHASE_AWAY                    = 10785,  -- Swikastoqq is Moblinn. Swikastoqq wentt to chase away badd Moblinns.
        HUH_BUT_WHAT_WERE_YOU_THINKING_GOING_OUT                                = 10786,  -- Huh... But, what were you thinking going out there again. You could've been hurt...or even worse!
        OH_I_M_SORRY_LET_ME_INTRODUCE_YOU                                       = 10787,  -- Oh, I'm sorry. Let me introduce you. This is my cutie Gobli--I mean Moblin buddy.
        SHE_CAME_BACK_HERE_RIGHT_AFTER_YOU_LEFT                                 = 10788,  -- She came back here right after you left. She said that something happened on the cape, but I couldn't get her to tell me what it was.
        I_DIDN_T_WANT_THE_OTHER_TOWNSPEOPLE_TO                                  = 10789,  -- I didn't want the other townspeople to worry, so I've been hiding her in this vacant storage room.
        BADD_MOBLINNS_WANTEDD_TO_KEEPP_SECRETTS_OF_SITE                         = 10790,  -- Badd Moblinns wantedd to keepp secretts of site to themselves.
        THATT_S_WHY_THEY_TRIEDD_TO_KILL_SWIKASTOQQ                              = 10791,  -- Thatt's why they triedd to kill Swikastoqq!
        THISS_MAPP_IS_FORR_EVERYONE_VANA_DIELL_IS                               = 10792,  -- Thiss mapp is forr everyone! Vana'diell is forr everyone!
        SO_I_GIVE_TAVNAZIA_LADY_MAPP                                            = 10793,  -- So I give Tavnazia lady mapp.
        ANDD_I_GIVE_OTHERR_MOBLINNS_MAPP_TOO_I                                  = 10794,  -- Andd I give otherr Moblinns mapp, too. I give everyone mapp!
        BUT_ARE_YOU_GOING_TO_BE_OKAY_WHAT                                       = 10795,  -- But are you going to be okay? What will happen if you go back to your hometown? You can always stay here with me...
        SWIKASTOQQ_IS_MOBLINN_MOBLINNS_LIVE_UNDERGROUNDD                        = 10796,  -- Swikastoqq is Moblinn. Moblinns live undergroundd.
        SWIKASTOQQ_WANTEDD_TO_KNOW_MORE_ABOUTT_UPWORLDD_SO                      = 10797,  -- Swikastoqq wantedd to know more aboutt upworldd, so Swikastoqq leftt home.
        JOURNEY_WASS_HARDD_JOURNEY_WASS_LONELY_BUTT_SWIKASTOQQ                  = 10798,  -- Journey wass hardd. Journey wass lonely. Butt Swikastoqq hadd funn. Swikastoqq wantss to telll Moblinns aboutt funn.
        I_GUESS_IF_THAT_S_YOUR_DREAM_I                                          = 10799,  -- I guess if that's your dream, I'm not going to stand here and hold you down. Be seeing you around, Swikastoq!
        YOU_KNOW_I_REALLY_DIDN_T_DO_ANYTHING                                    = 10800,  -- You know. I really didn't do anything at all. I don't deserve this map... Here, you take it.
        YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_RIGHT_THEN_MAYBE_THIS                              = 10801,  -- You're an adventurer, right? Then maybe this map is better served in your hands? What? You've already got one? Then I'll hold onto it in case some other lost soul comes wandering by.
        AND_IF_IN_YOUR_TRAVELS_YOU_EVER_SEE                                     = 10802,  -- And if in your travels you ever see my buddy again, tell her that I said hi...and that I hope I can see her again someday...
        I_WONDER_IF_MY_LITTLE_BUDDY_S_OKAY                                      = 10803,  -- I wonder if my little buddy's okay...
        AH_WHAT_AM_I_WORRIED_ABOUT_SHE_S                                        = 10804,  -- Ah, what am I worried about. She's got more brains in her pinky than I do in my pocket! She'll make it back to her hometown. I'm sure of it!
        IT_IS_NOT_ONLY_THE_ADULTS_OF_THE                                        = 10805,  -- It is not only the adults of the safehold who wish to improve our current situation--many of the younger men and women are also trying to make a difference.
        HOWEVER_WHAT_THEY_FAIL_TO_REALIZE_IS_THAT                               = 10806,  -- However, what they fail to realize is that cowering behind the walls of the city won't change anything...
        MY_NAME_IS_FERCHINNE_I_WAS_TIRED_OF                                     = 10807,  -- My name is Ferchinne. I was tired of seeing my people suffer, so I decided to journey forth from the confines of the safehold in order to earn the title of Dragon Slayer.
        I_TRAINED_FOR_MANY_MONTHS_BUT_I_FEEL                                    = 10808,  -- I trained for many months, but I feel I still lack the skills needed to defeat a truly horrifying dragon. To be a true Dragon Slayer, one must be able to soar like a dragon, not only physically, but mentally.
        PERHAPS_I_NEED_WINGS_OF_MY_OWN_TO                                       = 10809,  -- Perhaps I need wings of my own to catch the winds of the endless skies...
        THE_CITY_ELDERS_TOLD_ME_THAT_ONCE_LONG                                  = 10810,  -- The city elders told me that once, long ago, there were knights in the Kingdom of San d'Oria that could fly as high as the clouds.
        BRAVE_ADVENTURER_HAVE_YOU_EVER_SEEN_A_NOBLE                             = 10811,  -- Brave adventurer, have you ever seen a noble bird that walks on four legs? A proud beast that has the wings of an eagle?
        IF_YOU_COME_ACROSS_ONE_OF_THESE_MYTHICAL                                = 10812,  -- If you come across one of these mythical creatures, I would greatly appreciate it if you removed its tailfeathers and brought them back here to me.
        IT_IS_SAID_THAT_WHILE_THOSE_FEATHERS_ARE                                = 10813,  -- It is said that while those feathers are unbelievably light, they are remarkably sturdy. If I were to bond them together with wax, I could make wings of my own!
        BRING_BACK_TWO_AND_I_WILL_REWARD_YOU                                    = 10814,  -- Bring back two and I will reward you with something special.
        THE_LUSTER_THE_TOUCH_YES_THESE_ARE_THE                                  = 10815,  -- The luster, the touch... Yes, these are the feathers that I have been searching for. Thank you so very much. Now, maybe I can fly as high as the dragons themselves!
        HERE_TAKE_THIS_AS_A_TOKEN_OF_MY                                         = 10816,  -- Here, take this as a token of my appreciation.
        I_WAS_GIVEN_THAT_STONE_BY_AN_OLD                                        = 10817,  -- I was given that stone by an old merchant while traveling through the Eastern empire. He told me that it had the power to dissolve the clouds and rob mighty dragons of their ability to fly.
        BUT_EVEN_IF_IT_DOES_NOT_HAVE_THAT                                       = 10818,  -- But even if it does not have that power, I'm sure you can find someone who will purchase it from you for a large sum of gil.
        SIGH_WILL_I_EVER_BE_ABLE_TO_FLY                                         = 10819,  -- <Sigh> Will I ever be able to fly... Perhaps I need more feathers...
        I_AM_SORRY_TO_BOTHER_YOU_AGAIN_BUT                                      = 10820,  -- I am sorry to bother you again, but if you come across any more of the legendary tailfeathers, I beg of you to bring them to me.
        THANK_YOU_KIND_SIR_ADVENTURER                                           = 10821,  -- Thank you, kind sir/adventurer].
        OH_WHATEVER_AM_I_TO_DO                                                  = 10822,  -- Oh, whatever am I to do...?
        EXCUSE_ME_BUT_DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_COULD                                    = 10823,  -- Excuse me, but do you think you could help me?
        I_WAS_GOING_TO_GIVE_AN_OFFERING_TO                                      = 10824,  -- I was going to give an offering to the Goddess for my dear friend who passed away three years ago. However, the hairpin I was to offer is missing.
        I_KNOW_YOU_MUST_BE_BUSY_WITH_YOUR                                       = 10825,  -- I know you must be busy with your adventuring, but if you happen to spot it, please bring the hairpin back to me. I would be extremely grateful.
        LADY_ELYSIA_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_ALL_THE                                  = 10826,  -- Lady Elysia, what are you doing all the way down here?
        P_PRADIULOT                                                             = 10827,  -- P-Pradiulot!
        I_UH_I_WAS_LISTENING_TO_THE_TALES                                       = 10828,  -- I...uh... I was listening to the tales of this adventurer.
        HMPH_TALES                                                              = 10829,  -- Hmph, tales...
        SIR_MA_AM_THIS_MAY_SEEM_LIKE_AN                                         = 10830,  -- Sir/Ma'am], this may seem like an odd question, but...
        WE_HAVE_NOT_MET_BEFORE_HAVE_WE                                          = 10831,  -- We have not met before, have we?
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_BEING_SO_ABRUPT                                         = 10832,  -- I apologize for being so abrupt.
        DURING_THE_GREAT_WAR_TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_I                                 = 10833,  -- During the Great War twenty years ago, I suffered a terrible injury and lost all my memories of the past.
        THAT_IS_WHY_EVERY_TIME_I_MEET_SOMEONE                                   = 10834,  -- That is why every time I meet someone new, I ask them if we ever met.
        PRADIULOT_ARE_YOU_ON_PATROL                                             = 10835,  -- Pradiulot, are you on patrol?
        HM_AH_YES_ONE_LAST_CIRCLE_OF_THE                                        = 10836,  -- Hm? Ah, yes. One last circle of the area near the altar and I will be done.
        OH                                                                      = 10837,  -- Oh...
        WELL_AS_MUCH_AS_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO                                         = 10838,  -- Well, as much as I would like to stay and hear the tales of your journeys, I must finish my rounds. Good day, sir/ma'am].
        OH_AND_ELYSIA                                                           = 10839,  -- Oh, and Elysia...
        MIGHT_WE_HAVE_STEW_TONIGHT_I_DO_LOVE                                    = 10840,  -- Might we have stew tonight? I do love your homemade stew.
        OF_COURSE_PRADIULOT                                                     = 10841,  -- Of course, Pradiulot.
        AH_I_M_SORRY_FOR_A_MOMENT_THERE                                         = 10842,  -- ...... Ah, I'm sorry. For a moment there I was lost in thought...
        YES_THE_HAIRPIN_I_MIGHT_HAVE_DROPPED_IT                                 = 10843,  -- Yes, the hairpin. I might have dropped it while carrying groceries from the upper level of the safehold.
        I_DO_HOPE_YOU_ARE_ABLE_TO_FIND                                          = 10844,  -- I do hope you are able to find it...
        I_MIGHT_HAVE_DROPPED_THE_HAIRPIN_WHILE_CARRYING                         = 10845,  -- I might have dropped the hairpin while carrying groceries from the upper level of the safehold. I do hope you are able to find it...
        THERE_IS_NOTHING_OUT_OF_THE_ORDINARY_HERE_2                             = 10846,  -- There is nothing out of the ordinary here.
        YOU_FOUND_IT_I_WAS_BEGINNING_TO_THINK                                   = 10847,  -- You found it! I was beginning to think I would never see this again. Thank you so much...
        KIND_ADVENTURER_DO_YOU_HAVE_A_MOMENT                                    = 10848,  -- Kind adventurer, do you have a moment?
        I_TOLD_YOU_BEFORE_THAT_I_WAS_GOING                                      = 10849,  -- I told you before that I was going to present this hairpin as an offering to the Goddess.
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_I_LOST_ONE_OF_MY                                       = 10850,  -- Twenty years ago, I lost one of my dear friends to the flames of the Great War.
        NO_THE_WAR_DID_NOT_TAKE_HER_LIFE                                        = 10851,  -- No... The war did not take her life...
        IT_WAS_I_WHO_KILLED_HER                                                 = 10852,  -- It was I who killed her.
        MISCHANAU_HAD_JUST_MARRIED_BUT_SHE_WAS_VERY                             = 10853,  -- Mischanau had just married, but she was very weak. While her husband, a member of the Tavnazian Knights, was on duty, I would often visit her residence and take care of her.
        HOWEVER_ONE_DAY_THE_BEASTMEN_ARMIES_BROKE_THROUGH                       = 10854,  -- However, one day, the beastmen armies broke through the city's defenses and began their plundering and pillaging. I grabbed my friend's hand and began to flee with all the rest of the townspeople.
        AND_THAT_S_WHEN_IT_HAPPENED                                             = 10855,  -- And that's when it happened...
        OVERCOME_BY_THE_CROWDS_OF_PEOPLE_TRYING_TO                              = 10856,  -- Overcome by the crowds of people trying to escape the Orcs' arrows, I accidentally let go of Mischanau, and she was swallowed by the ocean of screaming women and children that spread in all directions.
        AFTER_THE_BATTLE_HAD_DIED_DOWN_I_ATTEMPTED                              = 10857,  -- After the battle had died down, I attempted to return to the city to find my dear friend, but I was stopped by the others.
        I_NEVER_SAW_MISCHANAU_AGAIN                                             = 10858,  -- ... I never saw Mischanau again...
        SINCE_THEN_NOT_A_DAY_HAS_GONE_BY                                        = 10859,  -- Since then, not a day has gone by that I haven't seen her in my dreams...calling out my name... And that is why every year around this time I take this hairpin of hers to the Altar of the Dawn and pray... Pray that she can forgive me for the pain I caused her...
        BEFORE_I_GO_TO_THE_ALTAR_MAY_I                                          = 10860,  -- Before I go to the altar, may I ask you one more favor?
        WOULD_YOU_FIND_PRADIULOT_AND_TELL_HIM_THAT                              = 10861,  -- Would you find Pradiulot and tell him that I will be waiting for him by the well?
        THANK_YOU_AGAIN                                                         = 10862,  -- Thank you again...
        HAVE_YOU_FOUND_PRADIULOT_AND_TOLD_HIM_THAT                              = 10863,  -- Have you found Pradiulot and told him that I will be waiting for him by the well?
        AH_THE_ADVENTURER_FROM_THE_MAINLAND_MAY_I                               = 10864,  -- Ah, the adventurer from the mainland. May I help you?
        ELYSIA_IS_WAITING_FOR_ME_BY_THE_WELL                                    = 10865,  -- Elysia is waiting for me by the well? Whatever could be wrong...?
        I_M_SORRY_THAT_I_ASKED_YOU_TO                                           = 10866,  -- I'm sorry that I asked you to do that.
        IT_IS_JUST_THAT_I_DON_T_WANT                                            = 10867,  -- It is just that I don't want him to see me when I make the offering for Mischanau.
        I_HAVEN_T_BEEN_COMPLETELY_HONEST_WITH_YOU                               = 10868,  -- I haven't been completely honest with you.
        BEFORE_SHE_DIED_MISCHANAU_S_HUSBAND                                     = 10869,  -- Before she died, Mischanau's husband...
        WAS_PRADIULOT                                                           = 10870,  -- ...was Pradiulot.
        HOWEVER_BECAUSE_OF_THE_INJURY_HE_SUSTAINED_DURING                       = 10871,  -- However, because of the injury he sustained during the war, he no longer remembers anything about her.
        MISCHANAU_WAS_MY_BEST_FRIEND_AND_I_WAS                                  = 10872,  -- Mischanau was my best friend, and I was elated when I heard the news of her marriage.
        EVEN_IF_THE_GROOM_WAS_MY_CHILDHOOD_FRIEND                               = 10873,  -- Even if the groom was my childhood friend...and sweetheart... I truly did wish them eternal happiness from the bottom of my heart.
        BUT_MAYBE_THERE_WAS_A_PART_OF_MY                                        = 10874,  -- But maybe there was a part of my heart that secretly despised my friend for stealing Pradiulot away from me... And maybe that is why I let go of her twenty years ago...
        I_COULD_NOT_LIVE_WITH_THIS_SIN_BEARING                                  = 10875,  -- I could not live with this sin bearing down upon my soul...
        SO_WHEN_THE_INJURED_PRADIULOT_WOKE_FROM_HIS                             = 10876,  -- So, when the injured Pradiulot woke from his coma, I told him everything that happened. However, by then it was too late. He no longer remembered me--or his late wife.
        I_DO_NOT_KNOW_WHAT_WILL_BECOME_OF                                       = 10877,  -- I do not know what will become of Pradiulot's memory in the future, but until he has fully recovered, I have chosen to stand by his side.
        THIS_I_FEEL_IS_THE_ONLY_WAY_I                                           = 10878,  -- This, I feel, is the only way I can pay for my terrible sins...
        THANK_YOU_AGAIN_FOR_ALL_THAT_YOU_HAVE                                   = 10879,  -- Thank you again for all that you have done for me. I do not know how I can repay you.
        I_MUST_LEAVE_BEFORE_PRADIULOT_RETURNS_PLEASE_TAKE                       = 10880,  -- I must leave before Pradiulot returns. Please take this as a token of my gratitude.
        I_HOPE_THAT_IT_CAN_AID_YOU_IN                                           = 10881,  -- I hope that it can aid you in your future travels.
        ELYSIA_WAS_NOT_AT_THE_WELL                                              = 10882,  -- Elysia was not at the well.
        WHAT_SHE_CAME_BY_TO_SAY_THAT_SHE                                        = 10883,  -- What? She came by to say that she did not need to see me at all?
        SOMETIMES_I_JUST_CANNOT_UNDERSTAND_THAT_WOMAN_IF                        = 10884,  -- Sometimes I just cannot understand that woman... If you see her again, tell her that tonight's stew had better be sublime if she wishes I forgive her!
        PRADIULOT_WAS_THAT_UPSET_WELL_I_GUESS_I                                 = 10885,  -- Pradiulot was that upset? Well, I guess I had better start working on that stew!
        GREETINGS_ADVENTURER_DID_YOU_SPEAK_WITH_ELYSIA_AGAIN                    = 10886,  -- Greetings, adventurer. Did you speak with Elysia again? Excellent. Now I have something to look forward to when I am relieved of duty.
        IF_YOU_DO_NOT_MIND_ME_ASKING_WHAT                                       = 10887,  -- If you do not mind me asking, what did you speak of with her?
        SIGH_ELYSIA_IS_A_KIND_KIND_WOMAN_WHEN                                   = 10888,  -- <Sigh> Elysia is a kind, kind woman. When I was on my deathbed, she stayed by my side for three whole days and three whole nights, tending to my wounds until I recovered from my coma.
        HER_HEART_IS_AS_PURE_AS_THE_CLEAR                                       = 10889,  -- Her heart is as pure as the clear waters of Cascade Edellaine.
        I_HAVE_NEVER_MET_A_WOMAN_SO_GENTLE                                      = 10890,  -- I have never met a woman so gentle and so sincere...
        AND_PERHAPS_THAT_IS_HER_ONLY_FAULT                                      = 10891,  -- And perhaps that is her only fault...
        LET_ME_TELL_YOU_A_STORY                                                 = 10892,  -- Let me tell you a story.
        LONG_AGO_THERE_WAS_A_BOY_WHO_HAD                                        = 10893,  -- Long ago, there was a boy who had a wonderful treasure so important to him that he always kept it by his side.
        THE_TREASURE_WAS_SO_DEAR_TO_HIM_THAT                                    = 10894,  -- The treasure was so dear to him that one day, when he had to go on a long journey, he felt the only person he could trust with that treasure was his best friend.
        HOWEVER_WHILE_THE_BOY_WAS_AWAY_A_TERRIBLE                               = 10895,  -- However, while the boy was away, a terrible accident occurred and the treasure was lost forever.
        WHEN_THE_BOY_RETURNED_AND_FOUND_WHAT_HAD                                = 10896,  -- When the boy returned and found what had happened to his treasure, he hated his friend for not being able to protect the item. But deep inside, the boy knew that the loss of his treasure was not only the fault of his friend.
        HE_KNEW_THAT_HE_TOO_WAS_RESPONSIBLE                                     = 10897,  -- He knew that he, too, was responsible...
        HOWEVER_AS_LONG_AS_THE_LOSS_OF_THE                                      = 10898,  -- However, as long as the loss of the treasure remained in the boy's heart, he knew that his friend would forever suffer with the pain of not fulfilling his promise.
        THE_BOY_DID_NOT_WISH_THIS_OF_HIS                                        = 10899,  -- The boy did not wish this of his longtime companion.
        AND_SO_HE_CHOSE_TO_LOSE_HIS_MEMORY                                      = 10900,  -- And so he chose to lose his memory.
        THIS_MAY_SOUND_RIDICULOUS_BUT_TO_THE_BOY                                = 10901,  -- This may sound ridiculous, but to the boy this was the only way to ease the suffering of his friend, as well as his own.
        BY_CHOOSING_TO_FORGET_ABOUT_THE_PAST_IT                                 = 10902,  -- By choosing to forget about the past, it could no longer hurt him or his friend.
        AND_SO_HE_LIVED_IN_HAPPINESS_UNTIL_THE                                  = 10903,  -- And so he lived in happiness, until the day he died...
        AH_I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_MY_BABBLING                                          = 10904,  -- Ah, I apologize for my babbling.
        FAREWELL_TRAVELER_I_HOPE_THAT_YOU_TOO_CAN                               = 10905,  -- Farewell, traveler. I hope that you, too, can find joy in this world filled with sorrow.
        YOU_MUST_HAVE_HAD_A_LONG_TIRING_JOURNEY                                 = 10906,  -- You must have had a long, tiring journey. I'm sorry our town doesn't have that much to offer...
        THE_SHIPS_FROM_JEUNO_BRING_IN_ALL_SORTS                                 = 10907,  -- The ships from Jeuno bring in all sorts of produce and spices. My kitchen shelves will never be bare again!
        ALL_CLEAR_DAY_IN_AND_DAY_OUT_IT                                         = 10908,  -- All clear... Day in and day out, it is always all clear... However, I guess I cannot complain...
        LATELY_THERE_HAS_BEEN_AN_INCREASE_IN_THE                                = 10909,  -- Lately there has been an increase in the number of outsiders utilizing our safehold's facilities. More ruffians means more crime...and that is what I am here to prevent.
        I_M_A_TRAVELING_MOOGLE_KUPO_I_HELP                                      = 10910,  -- I'm a traveling moogle, kupo. I help adventurers in the Outlands access items they have stored in a Mog House elsewhere, kupo.
        THIS_ISN_T_A_MOG_HOUSE_SO_YOU                                           = 10911,  -- This isn't a Mog House, so you can only use the Mog Safe, Change Jobs, and Delivery Box commands, kupo.
        YOU_HAVE_TO_PAY_FEE_OF_GIL_TO                                           = 10912,  -- You have to pay fee of # gil to transfer your items to the Outlands, kupo. Why? Because the world is a cold place for rogue moogles, kupo.
        OF_COURSE_YOU_CAN_MOVE_YOUR_ITEMS_BACK                                  = 10913,  -- Of course, you can move your items back to your Mog House in town, but if you want to transfer them to the Outlands again, you'll have to pay another fee, kupo. I've got to make a living too, kupo.
        TRANSFER_ITEMS_CURRENT_GIL_PAY_GIL_DON_T                                = 10914,  -- Transfer items? (Current gil:#) Pay # gil. Don't transfer items.
        YOU_DON_T_HAVE_ENOUGH_GIL_KUPO                                          = 10915,  -- You don't have enough gil, kupo.
        ITEM_TRANSFER_COMPLETE_KUPO                                             = 10916,  -- Item transfer complete, kupo.
        ID_10917                                                                = 10917,  -- # , #
        HELLO_TRAVELER_PLEASE_HAVE_A_LOOK_AT_THESE                              = 10918,  -- Hello, traveler! Please have a look at these fine Tavnazian-built products!
        HIDELY_HOWDY_HO_I_LL_SELL_YOU_WHAT                                      = 10919,  -- Hidely-howdy-ho! I'll sell you what I've got if you fork over enough dough!
        DO_YOU_NEED_ANY_TAVNAZIAN_PRODUCE_WE_DON                                = 10920,  -- Do you need any Tavnazian produce? We don't have much, but find a fine cook and your problems will be solved!
        DO_YOU_NEED_ANY_TAVNAZIAN_PRODUCE_SINCE_THE                             = 10921,  -- Do you need any Tavnazian produce? Since the arrival of the aid from Jeuno, our inventory has almost doubled!
        WELCOME_I_M_SORRY_THAT_WE_DON_T                                         = 10922,  -- Welcome. I'm sorry that we don't have more to offer, but...
        WELCOME_THANKS_TO_THE_SUPPLIES_FROM_JEUNO_I                             = 10923,  -- Welcome! Thanks to the supplies from Jeuno, I've been able to fix some of the weapons I had in storage!
        HELLO_AS_MUCH_AS_WE_D_LIKE_TO                                           = 10924,  -- Hello. As much as we'd like to sell you all the equipment we have in our warehouses, there is just not enough...
        HELLO_WITH_THE_ARRIVAL_OF_SUPPLIES_FROM_JEUNO                           = 10925,  -- Hello! With the arrival of supplies from Jeuno, we are now able to sell some of the items we had stored in these warehouses.
        GREETINGS_ADVENTURER_I_MAY_HAVE_A_FEW_THINGS                            = 10926,  -- Greetings, adventurer. I may have a few things that could be of interest.
        GREETINGS_ADVENTURER_I_VE_BEEN_GIVEN_AUTHORIZATION_TO                   = 10927,  -- Greetings, adventurer! I've been given authorization to begin the sale of the old Tavnazian armor we had in storage!
        PLEASE_SIR_MA_AM_WOULD_YOU_BUY_SOMETHING                                = 10928,  -- Please, sir/ma'am]. Would you buy something from my humble shop? I have five children to feed...
        PLEASE_SIR_MA_AM_EVEN_WITH_THE_AID                                      = 10929,  -- Please, sir/ma'am]. Even with the aid from Jeuno, I still have trouble feeding my six children...
        THE_SAFEHOLD_WAREHOUSES_USED_TO_STORE_A_GREAT                           = 10930,  -- The safehold warehouses used to store a great amount of equipment and supplies. However, now the rooms are almost completely bare...
        I_HAVE_BEEN_ASSIGNED_TO_WATCH_OVER_THE                                  = 10931,  -- I have been assigned to watch over the supplies in these storage rooms, though there is little to watch over...
        IF_WE_COULD_ONLY_MAKE_CONTACT_WITH_THE                                  = 10932,  -- If we could only make contact with the mainland... Then, maybe, the day would come when these warehouses are filled with goods from all over Vana'diel.
        MY_JOB_IS_TO_KEEP_INVENTORY_OF_THESE                                    = 10933,  -- My job is to keep inventory of these items. However, I have to count really, really slow or I finish in ten minutes!
        MY_LEGS_MAY_BE_SHORT_BUT_THEY_RE                                        = 10934,  -- My legs may be short, but they're faster than lightning! I guarantee I'll get your goods to where you want them to be!
        LITTLE_FOOD_LITTLE_SUPPLIES_THE_ONE_THING_TAVNAZIA                      = 10935,  -- Little food... Little supplies... The one thing Tavnazia does have a lot of, though, is storage space! <Sigh>
        I_CAN_SEND_YOUR_ITEMS_TO_ANYWHERE_IN                                    = 10936,  -- I can send your items to anywhere in Vana'diel!
        YOU_CAN_SET_THIS_AS_YOUR_CURRENT_HOME                                   = 10937,  -- You can set this as your current home point. Once you set a home point, you will return there whenever you are incapacitated.
        SET_THIS_AS_CURRENT_HOME_POINT_YES_NO                                   = 10938,  -- Set this as current home point? Yes. No.
        HOME_POINT_SET                                                          = 10939,  -- Home point set!
        A_HOME_POINT_CAN_BE_SET_AS_A                                            = 10940,  -- A home point can be set as a spot for you to return to Vana'diel when you have been knocked out. You can also use a home point to teleport to other home points.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_TRAVEL_TO_ANOTHER_HOME                                 = 10941,  -- What will you do? Travel to another home point. Set this as your home point. Other settings. On second thought, never mind.
        YOU_HAVE_REGISTERED_A_NEW_HOME_POINT_YOU                                = 10942,  -- You have registered a new home point! You are now able to teleport here from any other home point.
        YOU_MAY_TELEPORT_FROM_HERE_TO_ANY_OTHER                                 = 10943,  -- You may teleport from here to any other home point you have registered.
