        TELEPORT_WHERE_J_NOWHERE_HOME_POINT_1_HOME                              = 10945,  -- Teleport where?%j Nowhere. Home Point #1[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #2[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #3[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #4[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)]. Home Point #5[/ (M)/ (A)/ (E)].
        YOU_HAVE_NOT_YET_REGISTERED_ANY_OTHER_HOME                              = 10946,  -- You have not yet registered any other home points, and thus are unable to teleport.
        IT_COSTS_GIL_TO_TELEPORT_TO_HOME_POINT                                  = 10947,  -- It costs # gil to teleport to Home Point ## in %.
        THERE_IS_NO_FEE_FOR_TELEPORTING_TO_HOME                                 = 10948,  -- There is no fee for teleporting to Home Point ## in %.
        TELEPORT_CURRENT_GIL_YES_PLEASE_NO_THANK_YOU                            = 10949,  -- Teleport? (Current gil: #) [Add to favorites/Remove from favorites]. Yes, please. No, thank you.
        TELEPORT_TO_WHICH_REGION_ON_SECOND_THOUGHT_NONE                         = 10950,  -- Teleport to which region? On second thought, none. Select from favorites. Current region. [San d'Oria/Movalpolos]. [Bastok/Tavnazian Arch]. [Windurst/Lumoria]. [Jeuno/Mamool Ja Savage]. [Tavnazia/Halvung]. [West. Aht Urhgan/Arrapago Is]. [Adoulin Isles/Ruins of Alzadaal]. [Ronfaure/Ronfaure Front]. [Zulkheim/Norvallen Front]. [Norvallen/Gustaberg Front]. [Gustaberg/Derfland Front]. [Derfland/Sarutabaruta Front]. [Sarutabaruta/Aragoneu Front]. [Kolshushu/Fauregandi Front]. [Aragoneu/Valdeaunia Front]. [Fauregandi/East. Ulbuka]. [Valdeaunia/Ra'Kaznar]. [Qufim/]. [Li'Telor/]. [Kuzotz/]. [Vollbow/]. [Elshimo Low/]. [Elshimo Up/]. [Tu'Lia/]. Previous page. Next page.
        TELEPORT_WHERE_NONE_OF_THESE_A_FAVORITED_LOCATION                       = 10951,  -- Teleport where? None of these. A favorited location. An original area. A Rise of the Zilart area. A Chains of Promathia area. A Treasures of Aht Urhgan area. A Wings of the Goddess area. A Seekers of Adoulin area.
        YOU_MAY_CHANGE_THE_METHOD_OF_SELECTING_THE                              = 10952,  -- You may change the method of selecting the area of your desired home point to teleport to.
        WHICH_SETTING_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_MY_CURRENT_SETTING                         = 10953,  -- Which setting would you like? My current setting. Select by region. Select by expansion.
        YOU_ARE_NOW_SELECTING_BY                                                = 10954,  -- You are now selecting by [region/expansion].
        TELEPORT_WHERE_NONE_OF_THESE                                            = 10955,  -- Teleport where? None of these. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. [Add to favorites/Remove from favorites].
        HOME_POINT_IN_HAS_BEEN_YOUR_LIST_OF                                     = 10956,  -- Home Point ## in % has been [registered to/removed from] your list of favorite locations.
        YOUR_LIST_OF_FAVORITE_LOCATIONS_IS_FULL_YOU                             = 10957,  -- Your list of favorite locations is full. You must delete an existing entry in order to register a new one.
        DELETE_WHICH_NONE_OF_THESE                                              = 10958,  -- Delete which? None of these. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##. % ##.
        DO_YOU_FIND_OUR_ENCLOSED_CITY_STRANGE_THAT                              = 10959,  -- Do you find our enclosed city strange? That is probably because it is so different from what you have seen on the mainland.
        HOWEVER_FOR_US_THE_FORGOTTEN_THIS_CITY_IS                               = 10960,  -- However, for us--the forgotten--this city is all we know and all we have.
        SAFEHOLD_ELDER_DESPACHIAIRE_HAS_WELCOMED_THAT_ENVOY_FROM                = 10961,  -- Safehold elder Despachiaire has welcomed that envoy from Jeuno with open arms. However...
        I_HAVE_A_TERRIBLE_FEELING_SOMETHING_GRAVE_IS                            = 10962,  -- I have a terrible feeling something grave is upon us. Even those three menacing Tarutaru are acting strange...
        A_GREAT_CHALLENGE_AWAITS_YOU_IN_THE_SKIES                               = 10963,  -- A great challenge awaits you in the skies, %.
        BUT_I_CANNOT_HELP_BUT_THINK_IT_IRONIC                                   = 10964,  -- But I cannot help but think it ironic that a forgotten city such as ours would be the site of a battle that could alter the history of all Vana'diel.
        WHEN_I_HEARD_THAT_SOMEBODY_FROM_THE_MAINLAND                            = 10965,  -- When I heard that somebody from the mainland had washed up on our island, I was expecting to see a burly pirate or a battle-scarred adventurer.
        BUT_LOOK_AT_YOU_I_VE_SEEN_SCARIER                                       = 10966,  -- But look at you. I've seen scarier things under my bed. The world must be pretty peaceful if a pansy like you can travel about Vana'diel without getting his/her] head lopped off with an Orcish axe.
        DON_T_TELL_THIS_TO_ANYBODY_BUT_I                                        = 10967,  -- Don't tell this to anybody, but I don't think I like that blonde robed guy with the funny apparatus over his eye.
        HE_HAS_ALL_THE_ELDERS_WRAPPED_AROUND_HIS                                = 10968,  -- He has all the elders wrapped around his little finger, but something tells me he's trying to pull a fast one.
        IF_I_ONLY_HAD_PROOF                                                     = 10969,  -- If I only had proof...
        IF_YOU_EVEN_THINK_OF_DOING_ANYTHING_TO                                  = 10970,  -- If you even think of doing anything to make Prishe upset, I'll personally whack you upside the head so hard you won't remember what you had for breakfast.
        YEAH_SHE_MAY_BE_A_LITTLE_ROUGH_AROUND                                   = 10971,  -- Yeah, she may be a little rough around the edges, but deep inside she's only thinking of her friends and family here in the safehold.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_SOMETHING_BIG_S_BREWING                                   = 10972,  -- It looks like something big's brewing...
        I_VE_NEVER_BEEN_TOO_GOOD_WITH_WORDS                                     = 10973,  -- I've never been too good with words, but...
        GET_OUT_THERE_AND_DO_WHAT_YOU_HAVE                                      = 10974,  -- Get out there and do what you have to do. For the safehold's sake, for Prishe's sake...heck, for the world's sake!
        MAYBE_IT_S_BECAUSE_WE_VE_LIVED_IN                                       = 10975,  -- Maybe it's because we've lived in solitude for so long, but a lot of us have a hard time opening up to those from the outside.
        BUT_SINCE_YOU_CAME_THINGS_HAVE_STARTED_TO                               = 10976,  -- But since you came, things have started to change. Thanks, %...
        YOU_D_BETTER_HAVE_A_LOOK_AROUND_THE                                     = 10977,  -- You'd better have a look around the safehold while you can, because when our boss gets back, you might not be left with any legs to stand on.
        NO_I_M_NOT_TALKING_ABOUT_JUSTINIUS_SURE                                 = 10978,  -- No, I'm not talking about Justinius. Sure, he's the captain of the Tavnazian Patrol, but all final calls are made by the boss.
        YOU_LL_SEE_HEH_HEH_HEH                                                  = 10979,  -- You'll see... Heh heh heh...
        HUH_STILL_STANDING_I_SEE_I_THOUGHT_PRISHE                               = 10980,  -- Huh. Still standing, I see. I thought Prishe would have whipped you into a pile of crimson jelly by now.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_THE_BOSS_SEES                                         = 10981,  -- I don't know what the boss sees in you, but I'm not one to question her judgment.
        THE_SAFEHOLD_ELDER_HAS_BEEN_CALLING_PRISHE_THE                          = 10982,  -- The safehold elder has been calling Prishe the abhorrent one since I was knee-high to a bugard's eye.
        I_NEVER_ACTUALLY_KNEW_WHAT_HE_WAS_TRYING                                = 10983,  -- I never actually knew what he was trying to say...
        COME_TO_THINK_OF_IT_I_DON_T                                             = 10984,  -- Come to think of it, I don't even know what abhorrent means!
        YOU_RE_GOING_TO_SAVE_THE_BOSS_RIGHT                                     = 10985,  -- You're going to save the boss, right!?
        I_DIDN_T_THINK_MUCH_OF_YOU_BEFORE                                       = 10986,  -- I didn't think much of you before, and to tell you the truth, I don't think much of you now. But there is one thing I do know, and that is if anybody can help Prishe, it's you!
        I_KNEW_YOU_COULD_DO_IT_I_NEVER                                          = 10987,  -- I knew you could do it! I never doubted you for a minute! Hey, why don't you join the Tavnazian Patrol? I'd be honored to have a fine man/woman] like you working under me.
        HM_YOU_RE_NOT_DONE_WITH_YOUR_JOURNEY                                    = 10988,  -- Hm? You're not done with your journey yet? You adventurers have it hard, don't you?
        THERE_IS_A_YOUNG_GIRL_LIVING_HERE_WHO                                   = 10989,  -- There is a young girl living here who the elders all refer to as the abhorrent one.
        OH_DO_NOT_WORRY_YOU_WILL_KNOW_HER                                       = 10990,  -- Oh, do not worry. You will know her when you see her.
        EVERYONE_IN_THE_SAFEHOLD_ALWAYS_FOLLOWS_WHAT_PRISHE                     = 10991,  -- Everyone in the safehold always follows what Prishe says. Am I the only one who feels that this is even the slightest bit odd?
        SIR_JUSTINIUS_IS_THE_CAPTAIN_OF_THE_TAVNAZIAN                           = 10992,  -- Sir Justinius is the captain of the Tavnazian Patrol. He should have authority over all affairs concerning the city.
        HOWEVER_WHEN_IT_COMES_TO_MAKING_ANY_SORT                                = 10993,  -- However, when it comes to making any sort of decision, all the men run off to that despicable little girl.
        AH_PLEASE_DO_NOT_TELL_ANYONE_WHAT_I                                     = 10994,  -- Ah, please do not tell anyone what I just told you. If Tressia or Mengrenaux were to find out, my rations would be cut in half for a week...
        YOU_SEE_I_TOLD_YOU_PRISHE_WAS_A                                         = 10995,  -- You see, I told you Prishe was a terrible child.
        I_CAN_ASSURE_YOU_THAT_THERE_WILL_BE                                     = 10996,  -- I can assure you that there will be more problems to come as long as she remains in the safehold!
        A_BATTLE_WITH_THE_WYRMS_I_KNEW_THAT                                     = 10997,  -- A battle with the wyrms... I knew that Prishe would bring misfortune to our peaceful city...
        HOWEVER_I_HAVE_A_FEELING_THAT_YOU_AND                                   = 10998,  -- However, I have a feeling that you and our lea--and that dastardly child will be victorious in your efforts.
        OF_COURSE_I_DESPISE_HER_BUT_I_CANNOT                                    = 10999,  -- Of course I despise her, but I cannot deny that she is the strongest woman I have ever met.
        PRISHE_SURVIVED_THE_BATTLE_DID_SHE_NOT_EH                               = 11000,  -- Prishe survived the battle, did she not!? Eh? Me, worry about the abhorrent one? Do not be absurd...
        YOU_PROBABLY_WONDER_WHY_WE_HAVE_CHOSEN_TO                               = 11001,  -- You probably wonder why we have chosen to live our lives under the ground in these caves.
        THE_ROADS_LEADING_TO_THE_OLD_MARQUISATE_CAPITAL                         = 11002,  -- The roads leading to the old Marquisate capital have sunk to the bottom of the seas, and the surrounding meadows crawl with terrible beasts and remnants of the beastman armies.
        IT_IS_AMAZING_THAT_OUR_TINY_PATROL_IS                                   = 11003,  -- It is amazing that our tiny patrol is even able to maintain the peace in this small corner of the island...
        THE_SUDDEN_INFLUX_OF_VISITORS_FROM_JEUNO_HAS                            = 11004,  -- The sudden influx of visitors from Jeuno has left many of the safehold residents scared and confused. However, I welcome their presence as a blessing.
        I_DO_NOT_WISH_TO_BE_TIED_TO                                             = 11005,  -- I do not wish to be tied to this cursed place for the rest of my life...
        SO_YOU_PLAN_TO_WAGE_A_WAR_AGAINST                                       = 11006,  -- So you plan to wage a war against the Wyrmking and his minions? I apologize, but I fear the Tavnazian Patrol does not possess the manpower to assist you this time.
        HOWEVER_IN_YOUR_ABSENCE_WE_SHALL_ENSURE_THE                             = 11007,  -- However, in your absence we shall ensure the safety of the remaining safehold residents. Good luck, %.
        WELCOME_HOME_WE_ARE_ALL_RELIEVED_TO_SEE                                 = 11008,  -- Welcome home! We are all relieved to see you made it back unharmed.
        HOW_WAS_YOUR_RIDE_ON_THE_AIRSHIP_I                                      = 11009,  -- How was your ride on the airship? I had heard stories of the flying machines, but I never thought I would have the opportunity to see one up close.
        PERHAPS_SOME_DAY_I_WILL_BE_BLESSED_WITH                                 = 11010,  -- Perhaps some day I will be blessed with the opportunity to ride one as well...
        THAT_DOOR_OVER_THERE_LEADS_TO_THE_SAFEHOLD                              = 11011,  -- That door over there leads to the safehold elder Despachiaire's quarters.
        EVEN_NOW_ELDER_DESPACHIAIRE_BELIEVES_THAT_SOMEDAY_CARDINAL              = 11012,  -- Even now, elder Despachiaire believes that someday Cardinal Mildaurion will return to Tavnazia.
        THE_GREAT_CARDINAL_WHO_LED_OUR_FATHERS_OUT                              = 11013,  -- The great cardinal who led our fathers out of the flames of despair to this refuge... To us that were born after the Great War, stories of her are as distant as fairy tales.
        I_DON_T_UNDERSTAND_AFTER_YEARS_OF_FOLLOWING                             = 11014,  -- I don't understand... After years of following the words of the cardinal, how can the elder believe the utterings of a complete stranger?
        OR_MAYBE_HE_HAS_SIMPLY_RESORTED_TO_GRASPING                             = 11015,  -- Or maybe he has simply resorted to grasping at any thread of hope, no matter how thin...
        SINCE_ULMIA_S_DEPARTURE_DESPACHIAIRE_HAS_NOT_ONCE                       = 11016,  -- Since Ulmia's departure, Despachiaire has not once left his quarters.
        I_BELIEVE_I_NOW_KNOW_WHY_HE_WAS                                         = 11017,  -- I believe I now know why he was so quick to trust that Nag'molada.
        ALL_HE_WANTED_TO_DO_WAS_PROTECT_HIS                                     = 11018,  -- All he wanted to do was protect his granddaughter and the people of the safehold from suffering any more than they already had...
        THIS_IS_THE_MAIN_ENTRANCE_TO_THE_TAVNAZIAN                              = 11019,  -- This is the main entrance to the Tavnazian Safehold.
        THIS_IS_PRISHE_AND_ULMIA_S_ROOM                                         = 11020,  -- This is Prishe and Ulmia's room.
        I_D_KEEP_YOUR_DISTANCE_IF_YOU_KNOW                                      = 11021,  -- I'd keep your distance if you know what's good for you.
        IT_S_BEEN_KIND_OF_LONELY_WITHOUT_ULMIA                                  = 11022,  -- It's been kind of lonely without Ulmia or the boss around.
        I_SURE_HOPE_NOTHING_HAPPENS_TO_ULMIA                                    = 11023,  -- I sure hope nothing happens to Ulmia...
        AND_PRISHE_OH_I_KNOW_NOTHING_WILL_HAPPEN                                = 11024,  -- And Prishe? Oh, I know nothing will happen to Prishe. There isn't a jam she hasn't been able to find her way out of!
        YOU_SEE_I_TOLD_YOU_PRISHE_WOULD_BE                                      = 11025,  -- You see? I told you Prishe would be fine.
        BUT_I_D_SUGGEST_PUTTING_YOUR_ADVENTURES_ON                              = 11026,  -- But I'd suggest putting your adventures on hold for a while. We wouldn't want to make elder Despachiaire too upset...
        JUST_WHEN_I_THOUGHT_THEY_WERE_BACK_FOR                                  = 11027,  -- Just when I thought they were back for good, Ulmia and Prishe have run off again.
        I_WONDER_IF_THEY_LL_EVER_BE_BACK                                        = 11028,  -- I wonder if they'll ever be back...
        YOU_RE_ON_YOUR_WAY_TO_FIGHT_THE                                         = 11029,  -- You're on your way to fight the wyrms, aren't you? I really wish that Ulmia would reconsider going...
        BUT_SHE_WOULDN_T_LISTEN_TO_ME_WOULD                                     = 11030,  -- ...but she wouldn't listen to me, would she...
        BEYOND_THOSE_DOORS_LIE_THE_PHOMIUNA_AQUEDUCTS                           = 11031,  -- Beyond those doors lie the Phomiuna Aqueducts.
        THE_PHOMIUNA_AQUEDUCTS_ARE_CONNECTED_IN_MANY_PLACES                     = 11032,  -- The Phomiuna Aqueducts are connected in many places to the Tavnazian Cathedral's Sacrarium.
        HOWEVER_DURING_THE_GREAT_WAR_MANY_OF_THE                                = 11033,  -- However, during the Great War many of the hallways caved in, making them virtually impassable.
        IN_ADDITION_TO_THAT_CARDINAL_MILDAURION_PLACED_A                        = 11034,  -- In addition to that, Cardinal Mildaurion placed a powerful seal on the areas to weaken any beasts that remained in the halls and chambers.
        SHE_SACRIFICED_HER_LIFE_TO_HELP_THE_SURVIVORS                           = 11035,  -- She sacrificed her life to help the survivors of the burning city. We owe more than our lives to her...
        THE_DOOR_IS_LOCKED_TIGHT                                                = 11036,  -- The door is locked tight.
        THIS_CAVE_LEADS_TO_THE_SEALION_S_DEN                                    = 11037,  -- This cave leads to the Sealion's Den.
        THE_CAVE_WAS_ONCE_USED_AS_A_PRIVATE                                     = 11038,  -- The cave was once used as a private port for the Tavnazian Cathedral, but now...
        RECENTLY_WITH_ALL_THE_SUPPLY_SHIPS_FROM_JEUNO                           = 11039,  -- Recently, with all the supply ships from Jeuno coming and going, the port has been very active.
        THE_NATION_OF_JEUNO_HAS_OFFERED_ITS_HAND                                = 11040,  -- The nation of Jeuno has offered its hand to help lift up the ailing Tavnazia.
        NONE_OF_THIS_WOULD_HAVE_BEEN_POSSIBLE_WERE                              = 11041,  -- None of this would have been possible were it not for the kindness of Sir Nag'molada.
        I_DEEPLY_REGRET_NEVER_TELLING_MY_GRANDDAUGHTER_NOT                      = 11042,  -- I deeply regret never telling my granddaughter not to fraternize with that abhorrent Prishe.
        THEY_ARE_FROM_DIFFERENT_WORLDS_THEY_SHOULD_HAVE                         = 11043,  -- They are from different worlds... They should have remained separated.
        I_CAN_NO_LONGER_ALLOW_ULMIA_TO_BE                                       = 11044,  -- I can no longer allow Ulmia to be near those who are only out to deceive her.
        EVEN_IF_THAT_HAPPENED_TO_INCLUDE_AN_OUTSIDER                            = 11045,  -- Even if that happened to include an outsider such as you...
        IS_ULMIA_IS_MY_GRANDDAUGHTER_WELL                                       = 11046,  -- Is Ulmia... Is my granddaughter well?
        PLEASE_I_BEG_OF_YOU_DO_NOT_LET                                          = 11047,  -- Please... I beg of you, do not let anything harm her.
        I_HAVE_GIVEN_UP_TRYING_TO_HOLD_ULMIA                                    = 11048,  -- I have given up trying to hold Ulmia back.
        SHE_HAS_THE_RIGHT_TO_SEE_THE_WORLD                                      = 11049,  -- She has the right to see the world for what it is, and find the destiny that awaits her.
        I_NOW_REALIZE_THAT_MY_DUTY_AS_A                                         = 11050,  -- I now realize that my duty as a grandfather is not to control her, but to watch over her as she walks her own path.
        YOUNG_FOLK_THESE_DAYS_HAVE_BECOME_BLIND_TO                              = 11051,  -- Young folk these days have become blind to the light of Altana.
        THEY_DO_NOT_REALIZE_IT_IS_HER_BLESSING                                  = 11052,  -- They do not realize it is her blessing that fills this well with water for us to drink...
        MAY_ALTANA_HAVE_MERCY_ON_THEIR_PITIFUL_SOULS                            = 11053,  -- May Altana have mercy on their pitiful souls!
        AS_MUCH_AS_WE_D_LIKE_TO_REBUILD                                         = 11054,  -- As much as we'd like to rebuild the capital city of Tavnazia, I don't see it happening any time in the near future.
        THAT_PLACE_IS_CRAWLING_WITH_REMNANTS_OF_THE                             = 11055,  -- That place is crawling with remnants of the beastman army, all of them thirsty for the enemy's fresh blood...
        THE_TAVNAZIAN_AND_SAN_D_ORIAN_CATHEDRALS_BOTH                           = 11056,  -- The Tavnazian and San d'Orian Cathedrals both have roots in the same faith that originated centuries ago in the Elvaan kingdom.
        HOWEVER_UNDER_THE_GUIDANCE_OF_CARDINAL_MILDAURION_C                     = 11057,  -- However, under the guidance of Cardinal Mildaurion C Giloumet, the Tavnazian Cathedral eventually branched from the original teachings of the San d'Orian church and began to evolve separately.
        UNFORTUNATELY_THE_GREAT_WAR_PUT_AN_END_TO                               = 11058,  -- Unfortunately, the Great War put an end to any further development of the Marquisate's culture...
        NOW_THAT_JEUNO_HAS_REINSTATED_TIES_WITH_TAVNAZIA                        = 11059,  -- Now that Jeuno has reinstated ties with Tavnazia, it's only a matter of time before talks with the San d'Orian Cathedral are held.
        BUT_I_WONDER_IF_SAN_D_ORIA_WILL                                         = 11060,  -- But I wonder if San d'Oria will really offer to help us...
        THE_PHOMIUNA_AQUEDUCTS_THAT_CONNECT_THE_SAFEHOLD_WITH                   = 11061,  -- The Phomiuna Aqueducts that connect the safehold with the capital city of Tavnazia are a haven for monsters that feed on the flesh of unprepared travelers.
        HOWEVER_THANKS_TO_A_POWERFUL_SEAL_THE_CARDINAL                          = 11062,  -- However, thanks to a powerful seal the cardinal placed on the area twenty years ago, the power of the beasts is kept to a minimum.
        UNFORTUNATELY_THE_SEAL_ALSO_AFFECTS_ANYONE_ELSE_WHO                     = 11063,  -- Unfortunately, the seal also affects anyone else who journeys into the tunnels...
        THE_ABHORRENT_ONE_LIVES_AMONG_US_IT_IS                                  = 11064,  -- The abhorrent one lives among us... It is because of this that I often fear for the safety of my children and grandchildren...
        I_CAN_ONLY_PRAY_THAT_ALTANA_HAS_MERCY                                   = 11065,  -- I can only pray that Altana has mercy on those Tavnazians with pure souls...
        AND_STRIKES_DOWN_THOSE_WHO_BRING_DISASTER_TO                            = 11066,  -- ...and strikes down those who bring disaster to our humble city.
        THIS_SUPER_SPIFFY_SAFE_HOLD_USED_TO_BE                                  = 11067,  -- This super-spiffy safe-hold used to be filled with lots of se-cret rooms and hid-den sup-plies.
        BUT_NOW_THERE_S_HARD_LY_A_NY                                            = 11068,  -- But now there's hard-ly a-ny-thing left in this place, not coun-ting dust and cree-py-craw-ly cock-roa-ches, of course.
        I_E_VEN_HEARD_THAT_A_LONG_LONG                                          = 11069,  -- I e-ven heard that a long, long, long, long time a-go, the Tav-na-zian Ca-the-dral re-ceived a bunch of mur-der-ous-ly mys-ter-i-ous re-lics from the San d'Or-i-an Ca-the-dral.
        BUT_UN_LESS_IT_S_SOMETHING_TIP_PITY                                     = 11070,  -- But un-less it's something tip-pity-top tas-ty to munch on, I'm not that in-ter-rest-ed in any mus-ty old an-tiques.
        I_HAVE_HEARD_STORIES_FROM_PASSING_ADVENTURERS_CLAIMING                  = 11071,  -- I have heard stories from passing adventurers claiming all royal members of the Marquisate were killed during the Great War.
        IF_THIS_IS_TRUE_THEN_PERHAPS_THERE_IS                                   = 11072,  -- If this is true, then perhaps there is no hope for the future of the Pearl of Zafmlug.
        GODDESS_ALTANA_WHY_DO_YOU_TAKE_SO_MUCH                                  = 11073,  -- Goddess Altana! Why do you take so much, while in return only give so little!?
        I_WASHED_UP_ON_THE_SOUTHERN_BEACHES_OF                                  = 11074,  -- I washed up on the southern beaches of this island nearly seven years ago when my ship was destroyed in a terrible storm.
        IF_IT_WERE_NOT_FOR_THE_KINDNESS_OF                                      = 11075,  -- If it were not for the kindness of the people living here, I most surely would have met the same fate as my crewmates...
        WALK_THROUGH_THIS_HERE_CAVE_AND_YOU_LL                                  = 11076,  -- Walk through this here cave, and you'll find the headquarters of the Tavnazian Patrol. Travel a little bit further in, and you'll come by Prishe and Ulmia's quarters.
        ON_THE_OTHER_SIDE_OF_THIS_PASSAGEWAY_LIES                               = 11077,  -- On the other side of this passageway lies elder Despachiaire's private quarters, as well as the safehold well.
        BACK_THROUGH_HERE_YOU_LL_FIND_A_COUPLE                                  = 11078,  -- Back through here you'll find a couple of shops and a whole bunch of cutesy-wootsey, fuzzy-wuzzy moogles!
        THROUGH_THIS_CAVE_YOU_LL_FIND_A_NUMBER                                  = 11079,  -- Through this cave you'll find a number of storage rooms and warehouses, but most all of them are nearly empty...
        WE_VE_TRANSFORMED_THE_ONCE_EMPTY_WAREHOUSES_INTO                        = 11080,  -- We've transformed the once empty warehouses into auction houses and storage for delivery services. Have the days of glory finally returned to Tavnazia?
        YOU_ARE_AN_ADVENTURER_I_CAN_SMELL_THE                                   = 11081,  -- You are an adventurer... I can smell the dark blood of the undead as it drips slowly from your soiled garments.
        BEWARE_MY_FRIEND_FOR_YOU_ARE_NOT_ALONE                                  = 11082,  -- Beware, my friend, for you are not alone in your journey. Lost spirits lurk in the shadows behind you, waiting for their chance to rob you of your soul.
        HMMM_2                                                                  = 11083,  -- Hmmm...
        YOU_STILL_HAVE_A_FAIRLY_GOOD_HEAD_START                                 = 11084,  -- You still have a fairly good head start, but they will not let up until they have found you and filled your heart with poison and pain.
        THEY_ARE_CLOSE_IT_IS_ONLY_A_MATTER                                      = 11085,  -- They are close... It is only a matter of time before you have fallen within their reach.
        CAN_YOU_NOT_FEEL_THE_HANDS_THAT_REACH                                   = 11086,  -- Can you not feel the hands that reach up from the bottomless depths of hell? Can you not feel the gaze of a thousand eyes, glowing red with anger and hate?
        THE_GRIP_OF_EVIL_IS_TIGHTENING_ON_THE                                   = 11087,  -- The grip of evil is tightening on the very essence of what makes you who you are. Be forewarned, as it will not be long before you are confronted with a battle for more than just your life.
        OH_POOR_CHILD_MAY_THE_LIGHT_OF_THE                                      = 11088,  -- Oh, poor child! May the light of the Dawn Goddess lead you from the pitch-black depths of darkness!
        ALL_THE_ADULTS_SAY_IT_S_TOO_DANGEROUS                                   = 11089,  -- All the adults say it's too dangerous to go outside and play on the coast, but I'm sick of spending all day locked up in this cave.
        YEAH_I_WISH_WE_COULD_GO_OUT_ADVENTURING                                 = 11090,  -- Yeah, I wish we could go out adventuring like the Chebukkis!
        LO_OK_WHAT_MA_KKI_GA_VE_ME                                              = 11091,  -- Lo`ok what Ma`kki ga`ve me!t
        HEY_KUKKI_SAID_THAT_HE_WAS_GOING_TO                                     = 11092,  -- Hey! Kukki said that he was going to give that to me! I'm telling my mommy!
        I_WISH_I_WAS_OLDER_SO_I_COULD_2                                         = 11093,  -- I wish I was older so I could help my mom...
        SINCE_DAD_DIED_SHE_S_BEEN_SO_BUSY                                       = 11094,  -- Since Dad died, she's been so busy...
        CHERUKIKI_BROUGHT_MY_MOM_A_WHOLE_BARRELFUL_OF                           = 11095,  -- Cherukiki brought my mom a whole barrelful of supplies from the mainland.
        SHE_SAID_SHE_WAS_HAPPY_BUT_I_SAW                                        = 11096,  -- She said she was happy, but I saw her crying. I don't understand adults at all...
        I_FEEL_SORRY_FOR_THE_CHILDREN_ALL_COOPED                                = 11097,  -- I feel sorry for the children all cooped up here in the safehold, but it is just too dangerous to allow them to play outside.
        I_WILL_NOT_SAY_WHO_BUT_THERE_ARE                                        = 11098,  -- I will not say who, but there are three troublemakers who have taken it upon themselves to ignore this rule.
        AFTER_RETURNING_FROM_JEUNO_THOSE_TROUBLESOME_TARUTARU_PERSONALLY        = 11099,  -- After returning from Jeuno, those troublesome Tarutaru personally delivered a barrel of supplies to my quarters.
        MAYBE_I_WAS_WRONG_ABOUT_THEM                                            = 11100,  -- Maybe I was wrong about them...
        THE_OTHER_DAY_THOSE_THREE_TARUTARU_PRESENTED_ME                         = 11101,  -- The other day, those three Tarutaru presented me with the charred remains of some awful beast and told me to try it because it was mighty tasty.
        SINCE_THEY_WERE_CHILDREN_I_HAD_ALWAYS_TOLD                              = 11102,  -- Since they were children, I had always told the Chebukki brothers to never shun from a challenge, but to think I would be tested by my own words...
        DID_I_SHOW_YOU_WHAT_MAKKI_BROUGHT_ME                                    = 11103,  -- Did I show you what Makki brought me back from Jeuno? They are some of the most amazing things I have ever seen.
        ONE_OF_THEM_WAS_A_RARE_ITEM_MADE                                        = 11104,  -- One of them was a rare item made in the Far East, but I decided to give it to Yasuji. He said that he used to live in the Eastern empire before his ship wrecked...
        I_TELL_YA_ALL_THESE_HERE_YOUNG_FOLK                                     = 11105,  -- I tell ya, all these here young folk in the safehold ain't never had it hard--'specially those dangnabbed Tarutots!
        WHY_BACK_IN_MY_DAY_WE_HAD_TO                                            = 11106,  -- Why, back in my day, we had to fight through herds of wild bugards and Orc armies in the snow--with nothin' more than our bare fists--just to make it to the outhouse!
        WELL_WHADDAYA_KNOW_SOMEBODY_WENT_AN_DONE_TAUGHT                         = 11107,  -- Well, whaddaya know. Somebody went an' done taught those darn tootin' Tarutots some manners.
        WHY_THEY_EVEN_BROUGHT_ME_A_BRAND_SPANKIN                                = 11108,  -- Why, they even brought me a brand-spankin'-new pair of extra fancy wooden teeth from that Jeuno place they moseyed off to.
        THE_STAR_OF_TAV_NA_ZI_A_WELL                                            = 11109,  -- The Star of Tav-na-zi-a? Well, we can ass-ume from the name that it's some-thing that was kept in the mar-qui-sate.
        UN_FOR_TU_NATE_LY_I_CAN_T                                               = 11110,  -- Un-for-tu-nate-ly, I can't tell you much more. May-be some-bo-dy who used to work at the ca-the-dral knows some-thing.
        YOUNG_TRAVELER_YOU_DON_T_BELIEVE_THAT_THERE                             = 11111,  -- Young traveler, you don't believe that there is some great treasure hidden in the Sacrarium, do you?
        WELL_I_HATE_TO_BE_THE_ONE_WHO                                           = 11112,  -- Well, I hate to be the one who has to tell you this, but there's nothing but old rubbish left in that place--its rooms were raided and plundered years ago.
        THE_ARRIVAL_OF_THAT_ELVAAN_KNIGHT_REMINDED_ME                           = 11113,  -- The arrival of that Elvaan knight reminded me of a story my teacher used to tell us at grammar school.
        LONG_AGO_THERE_WAS_A_FRIGHTENINGLY_POWERFUL_JEWEL                       = 11114,  -- Long ago, there was a frighteningly powerful jewel hidden somewhere in the Marquisate, and to protect us from its evil, Cardinal Mildaurion had placed a powerful seal upon it. I wonder if that tale was true...
        BEFORE_THE_MARQUISATE_OF_TAVNAZIA_WAS_DESTROYED_THE                     = 11115,  -- Before the Marquisate of Tavnazia was destroyed, the region was a thriving center for commerce. Ships from all across Vana'diel would grace our nation's ports.
        HOWEVER_THE_MOST_PROMINENT_WERE_THOSE_FROM_THE                          = 11116,  -- However, the most prominent were those from the nations of the West. I remember one time a Western vessel carrying a mountain of gold ingots arrived in Tavnazia offering to purchase a jewel known as the something-or-other of Tavnazia.
        MY_LATE_BROTHER_WAS_ONCE_A_MEMBER_OF                                    = 11117,  -- My late brother was once a member of the Tavnazian choir. I remember him once telling me that there existed a lost hymn that not a single member of the Tavnazian Cathedral was able to sing.
        HE_SAID_IT_WAS_THE_WORDS_FROM_THAT                                      = 11118,  -- He said it was the words from that hymn that would save the children of Altana from their lives of suffering.
        THE_ELDER_DESPACHIAIRE_S_GRANDDAUGHTER_HAS_THE_MOST                     = 11119,  -- The elder Despachiaire's granddaughter has the most magnificent voice. It is as if you were hearing the whisper of the Dawn Goddess herself.
        HOWEVER_I_REMEMBER_THERE_BEING_ANOTHER_YOUNG_GIRL                       = 11120,  -- However, I remember there being another young girl in the Tavnazian choir who was just as talented as Lady Ulmia.
        IF_ONLY_LITTLE_EMELINE_HAD_SURVIVED_THE_BEASTMAN                        = 11121,  -- If only little Emeline had survived the beastman attack.
        READ_THE_SCRIPTURE_YES_NO                                               = 11122,  -- Read the scripture? Yes. No.
        LONG_LONG_AGO_AN_ANCIENT_RACE_DESCENDED_FROM                            = 11123,  -- Long, long ago, an ancient race, descended from the gods, flourished in Vana'diel.
        THEY_TRAVELED_THROUGH_THE_SKY_EXTRACTED_GOLD_FROM                       = 11124,  -- They traveled through the sky, extracted gold from stones, and gave birth to grasslands across the world.
        BUT_ONE_DAY_THEY_DECIDED_TO_BUILD_A                                     = 11125,  -- But one day, they decided to build a pathway to the divine entrance of Paradise.
        ENRAGED_BY_SUCH_A_BRAZEN_DISPLAY_OF_INSOLENCE                           = 11126,  -- Enraged by such a brazen display of insolence, the gatekeeper destroyed their path and cast their homes to the bottom of the sea.
        SHORTLY_THEREAFTER_THE_GODDESS_ALTANA_AWAKENED_AND_SAW                  = 11127,  -- Shortly thereafter, the goddess Altana awakened and saw the ruin that had once been Vana'diel. Saddened, She wept five divine tears.
        WHEN_THE_FIVE_TEARS_FELL_UPON_THE_EARTH                                 = 11128,  -- When the five tears fell upon the earth, they gave life to the five races of Vana'diel.
        BUT_THE_GOD_PROMATHIA_SAW_THIS_FROM_HIS                                 = 11129,  -- But the god Promathia saw this from His place in the shadows. The Twilight God saw fit to condemn Altana's work, cursing the people with eternal conflict amongst themselves.
        HE_CREATED_TERRIBLE_BEASTS_AND_SPREAD_THEM_ACROSS                       = 11130,  -- He created terrible beasts and spread them across the world, commanding them to fight the people of Vana'diel and occupy their minds.
        NEVER_AGAIN_WOULD_THEY_THINK_TO_OPEN_THE                                = 11131,  -- Never again would they think to open the Gate of the Gods.
        THIS_IS_THE_ENTRANCE_TO_THE_TAVNAZIAN_SAFEHOLD                          = 11132,  -- This is the entrance to the Tavnazian Safehold.
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_WE_WERE_ALL_OVERJOYED_WHEN                             = 11133,  -- Twenty years ago, we were all overjoyed when news of the allied forces' victory over the Shadow Lord's armies finally reached our island.
        HOWEVER_DEEP_INSIDE_WE_KNEW_THAT_THIS_WOULD                             = 11134,  -- However, deep inside we knew that this would only be a short-lived triumph. As long as there is light in the world, there will always exist darkness.
        FOR_THE_PAST_TWENTY_YEARS_NOT_A_DAY                                     = 11135,  -- For the past twenty years, not a day has gone by when the words of Cardinal Mildaurion haven't rung in my mind.
        THE_TALES_OF_THE_BEASTMEN_AND_THEIR_DEVILISH                            = 11136,  -- The tales of the beastmen and their devilish plan to bring their terrible god back to life, eradicating Vana'diel of mankind's seeds.
        SOMETIMES_AT_NIGHT_I_STILL_SEE_VISIONS_OF                               = 11137,  -- Sometimes at night, I still see visions of the battlefield I stood on twenty years ago. The cold eyes of the Kindred as they searched the landscape for their next victim...
        I_REMEMBER_HEARING_TALES_OF_HOW_THE_SHADOW                              = 11138,  -- I remember hearing tales of how the Shadow Lord called up these bloodthirsty beasts from the depths of hell, where their dark leader awaited in slumber...
        ONLY_IN_A_P_PLACE_LIKE_THIS_C                                           = 11139,  -- Only in a p-place like this c-can a m-m-m-man like m-m-m-me hide from the ridicule of the w-world.
        HM_OH_UM_YES_PAY_N_NO_HEED                                              = 11140,  -- Hm? Oh...um... Yes... Pay n-no heed t-to m-m-m-y ramblings...
        I_THOUGHT_THAT_IN_A_P_PLACE_LIKE                                        = 11141,  -- I thought that in a p-place like this, I m-m-m-might be able to hide from the r-ridicule of the w-world. However, n-now that Tavnazia has reopened its doors to the outside...
        B_BUT_YOU_UNDERSTAND_R_RIGHT_NO                                         = 11142,  -- B-but... You understand...r-right? No?
        I_NEVER_REALLY_NEEDED_A_MANNEQUIN_TO_REMIND                             = 11143,  -- I never really needed a mannequin to remind me how beautiful my Alsha was...is.
        THAT_S_RIGHT_FROM_NOW_ON_SHE_LL                                         = 11144,  -- That's right. From now on, she'll be here, right by my side...
        ARE_YOU_TRYING_TO_TELL_ME_YOU_HAVE                                      = 11145,  -- Are you trying to tell me you have lost...?
        HERE_YOU_MUST_LEARN_TO_CHERISH_THEM_WITH                                = 11146,  -- Here. You must learn to cherish them with all you heart.
        HAIL_THE_PROUD_AND_VALIANT_KNIGHTS_OF_TAVNAZIA_2                        = 11148,  -- Hail the proud and valiant knights of Tavnazia! Raise the pennants and cheer us on to victory!
        YOUR_BUSINESS_HERE_SIR_MADAME_YOU_SEEK_A                                = 11149,  -- Your business here, sir/madame]? You seek a young maiden and her airborne, alabaster companion?
        WHY_THE_LADY_IN_QUESTION_PASSED_MY_TRIAL                                = 11150,  -- Why, the lady in question passed my trial and joined our illustrious order, just as you did!
        WHY_THE_LADY_IN_QUESTION_PASSED_MY_TRIAL_2                              = 11151,  -- Why, the lady in question passed my trial and joined the Tavnazian order of knights!
        THE_FIERY_YOUNG_DAMSEL_IS_ON_A_QUEST                                    = 11152,  -- The fiery young damsel is on a quest to find the famous Goldmane!
        THUS_I_IMPARTED_TO_HER_THE_LOCATION_OF                                  = 11153,  -- Thus I imparted to her the location of the bounty hunter's birthplace!
        HE_WAS_RAISED_IN_A_SHEPHERD_S_VILLAGE                                   = 11154,  -- He was raised in a shepherd's village found in the west of the Tavnazian archipelago.
        THAT_LAND_IS_NOW_THE_SITE_OF_TREMENDOUS                                 = 11155,  -- That land is now the site of tremendous change brought about by fell sorcery!
        GOLDMANE_WAS_BORN_IN_THAT_QUIET_VILLAGE_BUT                             = 11156,  -- Goldmane was born in that quiet village, but was loath to follow the shepherd's path. After moving to Tavnazia, he took up the mercenary trade of the bounty hunter!
        WHEN_HE_MET_AND_MARRIED_A_LADY_MAGE                                     = 11157,  -- When he met and married a lady mage, however, Goldmane's footsteps led him back to the place of his birth to start a family.
        PEOPLE_WILL_ALWAYS_FIND_THEIR_WAY_BACK_TO                               = 11158,  -- People will always find their way back to the beginning. The same holds true when we reach the end of our path in life.
        YES_I_ONCE_WAS_A_MERCHANT_SELLING_TAVNAZIAN                             = 11159,  -- Yes, I once was a merchant selling Tavnazian crafts to the San d'Orian Cathedral. But that was long ago...
        HMPH_I_SUPPOSE_YOU_WONDER_HOW_A_MERE                                    = 11160,  -- Hmph... I suppose you wonder how a mere merchant rose to the position of safehold elder.
        THE_ANSWER_IS_SIMPLE_YOUNG_MAN_WOMAN_I                                  = 11161,  -- The answer is simple, young man/woman]. I have merely outlived all those more qualified.
        HOWEVER_DO_NOT_BE_MISTAKEN_NOT_ONCE_DID                                 = 11162,  -- However, do not be mistaken. Not once did I ask to be granted this position, and not once have I used it for any sort of personal gain.
        I_APOLOGIZE_I_SEEM_TO_HAVE_DIVERGED_FROM                                = 11163,  -- I apologize. I seem to have diverged from the matter at hand. Forget what you have heard... Just as I have forgotten the countless tribulations of my past...
        YES_YOU_WISHED_TO_INQUIRE_ABOUT_TAVNAZIAN_CUISINE                       = 11164,  -- Yes. You wished to inquire about Tavnazian cuisine. I suggest you speak with Jonette. She can be found with her daughter, down near the underground tributary.
        JONETTE_IS_WELL_KNOWN_THROUGHOUT_THE_SAFEHOLD_FOR                       = 11165,  -- Jonette is well known throughout the safehold for her undying interest in Tavnazian dishes. She will more than likely be able to answer any questions you may have on the subject.
        AH_YOU_WOULDN_T_HAPPEN_TO_BE_AN                                         = 11166,  -- Ah, you wouldn't happen to be an adventurer, would you? I usually avoid pestering others with my problems, but I find myself in a fix.
        RECENTLY_I_HAVE_BEGUN_STUDYING_TRADITIONAL_TAVNAZIAN_COOKING            = 11167,  -- Recently, I have begun studying traditional Tavnazian cooking methods.
        HOWEVER_OUR_LIBRARIES_CONTAIN_NO_BOOKS_ON_THE                           = 11168,  -- However, our libraries contain no books on the subject, and the mists of time have clouded the memories of the safehold elders.
        OUR_CURRENT_STATE_OF_AFFAIRS_LIMITS_THE_BOUNTY                          = 11169,  -- Our current state of affairs limits the bounty that we can bring to our children's plates. That is why I felt that rekindling the culinary arts of Tavnazia's past would rejuvenate the spirits of this cave's weary souls.
        YOU_WOULDN_T_HAVE_HAPPENED_TO_COME_ACROSS                               = 11170,  -- You wouldn't have happened to come across anything on your journey that may be of use, would you?
        IF_YOU_WERE_TO_FIND_SOMETHING_I_WOULD                                   = 11171,  -- If you were to find something, I would be so grateful...as would all the other safehold residents.
        THIS_IS_EXACTLY_THE_INFORMATION_I_HAVE_BEEN                             = 11172,  -- %! This is exactly the information I have been searching for!
        YOUR_KINDNESS_IS_A_BLESSING_THAT_WILL_BRING                             = 11173,  -- Your kindness is a blessing that will bring smiles to the dinner tables of Tavnazia.
        I_KNOW_IT_IS_NOT_MUCH_BUT_PLEASE                                        = 11174,  -- I know it is not much, but please accept this as a token of my appreciation.
        THE_INFORMATION_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_ME_ON_TAVNAZIAN                        = 11175,  -- The information you have brought me on Tavnazian cuisine has been a wonderful help!
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_FIND_ANY_MORE_THE                                      = 11176,  -- If you happen to find any more, the children would be so delighted.
        YOUR_FATE_RIDES_ON_THE_CHANGING_WINDS_OF                                = 11177,  -- Your fate rides on the changing winds of Vana'diel. I can give you insight on the local weather.
        WHAT_AREA_S_WEATHER_DO_YOU_WISH_TO                                      = 11178,  -- What area's weather do you wish to know? Nowhere. Ronfaure. La Theine Plateau. Valkurm Dunes. Jugner Forest. Batallia Downs. Gustaberg. Konschtat Highlands. Pashhow Marshlands. Rolanberry Fields. Beaucedine Glacier. Xarcabard. Cape Teriggan. Altepa Desert. Sarutabaruta. Tahrongi Canyon. Buburimu Peninsula. Meriphataud Mountains. Sauromugue Champaign. The Sanctuary of Zi'Tah. Yuhtunga & Yhoator Jungles. Qufim Island. Tu'Lia. Ferry. Airship. Jeuno. Uleguerand Range. Tavnazian Archipelago. Riverne - Sites #A01 & #B01.
