        A_STORAGE_FEE_OF_GIL_WILL_BE_REQUIRED                                   = 11210,  -- A storage fee of # gil will be required upon pickup of this particular set.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_FIGHTER_S_ARMOR_TEMPLE                                = 11211,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Fighter's Armor. Temple Attire. Healer's Attire. Wizard's Attire. Warlock's Armor. Rogue's Attire. Gallant Armor. Chaos Armor. Beast Armor. Choral Attire. Hunter's Attire. Myochin Armor. Ninja Garb. Drachen Armor. Evoker's Attire. Magus Attire. Corsair's Attire. Puppetry Attire. Dancer's Attire. Dancer's Attire. Scholar's Attire. Amir Armor Set. Pahluwan Armor Set. Yigit Armor Set.
        THE_STORAGE_FEE_FOR_YOUR_ARMOR_COMES_TO                                 = 11212,  -- The storage fee for your armor comes to # gil.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PAY_THE_FEE_NOT                                          = 11213,  -- Do you wish to pay the fee? Not at this time. Yes.
        I_AM_SORRY_SIR_MA_AM_GIL_IS                                             = 11214,  -- I am sorry, sir/ma'am]. # gil is required before we can return your armor.
        VERY_WELL_SIR_MA_AM_WHEN_YOU_WISH                                       = 11215,  -- Very well, sir/ma'am]. When you wish to have your armor returned, remember to present this claim slip along with the #-gil storage fee at any of our five convenient pickup locations around Vana'diel.
        REGULATIONS_DO_NOT_ALLOW_ADVENTURERS_TO_STORE_MORE                      = 11216,  -- Regulations do not allow adventurers to store more than one set of the same armor.
        THE_ITEMS_YOU_ATTEMPTED_TO_TRADE_HAVE_BEEN                              = 11217,  -- The items you attempted to trade have been returned.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_WARRIOR_S_ARMOR_MELEE                                 = 11218,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Warrior's Armor. Melee Attire. Cleric's Attire. Sorcerer's Attire. Duelist's Armor. Assassin's Attire. Valor Armor. Abyss Armor. Monster Armor. Bard's Attire. Scout's Attire. Saotome Armor. Koga Garb. Wyrm Armor. Summoner's Attire. Mirage Attire. Commodore Attire. Pantin Attire. Etoile Attire. Argute Attire.
        JUSTINIUS_IF_I_COULD_HAVE_A_MOMENT_OF                                   = 11219,  -- Justinius! If I could have a moment of your time...
        EH_WHY_OF_COURSE_CHEMIOUE_BUT_AS_YOU                                    = 11220,  -- Eh? Why of course, Chemioue. But as you can see, I am quite busy at the moment. Perhaps we could speak a little while later.
        AND_OF_HOW_MANY_HOURS_MIGHT_A_LITTLE                                    = 11221,  -- And of how many hours might a little while construe?
        I_AM_GOING_TO_NEED_A_LITTLE_MORE                                        = 11222,  -- I am going to need a little more time to come to a specific number...
        HMPH_IF_THAT_IS_THE_CASE                                                = 11223,  -- Hmph. If that is the case...
        YOU_HOW_LONG_HAVE_YOU_BEEN_STANDING_THERE                               = 11224,  -- ...You! How long have you been standing there?
        YOU_MUST_KNOW_THAT_IT_IS_QUITE_IMPOLITE                                 = 11225,  -- You must know that it is quite impolite to eavesdrop on a lady's private conversation! Why, now that I think of it, there is only one other person who would do something so atrocious... Prishe!
        YOU_KNOW_OF_WHOM_I_SPEAK_RECENTLY_A                                     = 11226,  -- You know of whom I speak. Recently, a day does not go by without the other safehold residents reveling over that hooligan's every action.
        PRISHE_REPAIRED_MY_SUBLIGAR_PRISHE_DUELED_AN_ORCISH                     = 11227,  -- Prishe repaired my subligar, Prishe dueled an Orcish Serjeant, Prishe saved my baby from a Megalobugard... Prishe, Prishe, Prishe, Prishe, Prishe!
        IF_I_HEAR_THAT_NAME_ONE_MORE_TIME                                       = 11228,  -- If I hear that name one more time, I am going to scream so loud, the Mithra in Kazham will have to cover their ears to prevent them from exploding!
        DO_NOT_MISTAKE_ME_I_KNOW_FULL_WELL                                      = 11229,  -- Do not mistake me. I know full well what that ruffian is capable of accomplishing.
        IT_IS_JUST_IT_IS_HOW_SHE_GOES                                           = 11230,  -- It is just... It is how she goes about making those accomplishments. Subtle is a word that was unfortunately torn from her dictionary the day she was born.
        AND_WHAT_OF_JUSTINIUS_OUR_FEARLESS_LEADER_IGNORES                       = 11231,  -- And what of Justinius? Our fearless leader ignores him like a chamber pot in the closet, leaving him to rot in the belly of this cave while she is off frolicking in the meadows!
        WHO_DOES_SHE_THINK_SHE_IS_JUST_BECAUSE                                  = 11232,  -- Who does she think she is!? Just because she had some terrible accident when she was a child does not give her the right to strut about the archipelago like she was the marquise!
        UNFORTUNATELY_MOST_PEOPLE_INCLUDING_POOR_JUSTINIUS_ARE_BLIND            = 11233,  -- Unfortunately, most people, including poor Justinius, are blind to the truth--that she is nothing more than a selfish little brat with a mouth filthier than the backside of my boot!
        YOU_AGREE_WITH_ME_DO_YOU_NOT_OR                                         = 11234,  -- You agree with me, do you not? Or have you been brainwashed like all the others--the wool pulled over your very sense of reasoning?
        DO_YOU_TRULY_BELIEVE_THAT_BRUTE_FORCE_AND                               = 11235,  -- Do you truly believe that brute force and raw ambition will lead us to Paradise?
        WELL_I_CERTAINLY_CANNOT_YOU_WILL_NOT_WITNESS                            = 11236,  -- Well, I certainly cannot. You will not witness me become a victim of that fiend's attempts at subjugation!
        CHEMIOUE                                                                = 11237,  -- Chemioue!
        YOU_RE_NOT_PREACHING_ABOUT_PRISHE_TO_THIS                               = 11238,  -- You're not preaching about Prishe to this outsider, are you?
        TR_TRESSIA_HOW_LONG_HAVE_YOU_BEEN_STANDING                              = 11239,  -- Tr-Tressia! How long have you been standing there?
        HOW_LONG_HAVE_YOU_SEEN_ME_STANDING_ANYWHERE                             = 11240,  -- How long? Have you seen me standing anywhere else?
        SIGH_2                                                                  = 11241,  -- <Sigh>...
        CHEMIOUE_WHEN_ARE_YOU_GOING_TO_PUT_ASIDE                                = 11242,  -- Chemioue, when are you going to put aside your feelings about Prishe and start concentrating on your duties?
        BUT_I_I                                                                 = 11243,  -- But I...I...
        AREN_T_YOU_SUPPOSED_TO_BE_ON_YOUR                                       = 11244,  -- Aren't you supposed to be on your rounds? Or were you so busy talking to this adventurer that you forgot?
        I_WAS_JUST                                                              = 11245,  -- I was just...
        WHEN_ARE_YOU_GOING_TO_GROW_UP_AND                                       = 11246,  -- When are you going to grow up and stop letting your emotions get in the way of things?
        WAIT_ONE_MOMENT_YOU_ARE_THE_LAST_PERSON                                 = 11247,  -- Wait one moment! You are the last person to tell someone they need to grow up! Why, just last week I remember you holding Mengrenaux in a headlock because he would not lend you his buckler.
        THAT_HAS_NOTHING_TO_DO_WITH_ANYTHING_WE                                 = 11248,  -- That has nothing to do with anything! We're talking about you and Prishe here, Chemioue. Stop trying to change the subject!
        CHANGE_THE_SUBJECT_WERE_IT_NOT_FOR_YOUR                                 = 11249,  -- Change the subject? Were it not for your meddling, there would be no subject of which to speak!
        MY_OPINIONS_ARE_MERELY_A_REFLECTION_OF_THE                              = 11250,  -- My opinions are merely a reflection of the discontent that dwells deep within the hearts of all Tavnazians.
        NOT_ONCE_HAVE_MY_FEELINGS_FOR_THAT_BLUE                                 = 11251,  -- Not once have my feelings for that blue-haired sea worm ever impaired my judgment! Never!
        HAH_HAH_HAH                                                             = 11252,  -- Hah hah hah!
        ARE_YOU_SUGGESTING_I_SPEAK_NOT_THE_TRUTH                                = 11253,  -- Are you suggesting I speak not the truth?
        LISTEN_UP_CHEMIOUE_I_COULD_CARE_LESS_IF                                 = 11254,  -- Listen up, Chemioue. I could care less if you swore on Eonnite's Revelations. That's not the point.
        THE_POINT_IS_UNLIKE_SNIFFLING_LITTLE_CHILDREN_ADULTS                    = 11255,  -- The point is, unlike sniffling little children, adults know when to keep their opinions to themselves.
        HMPH_2                                                                  = 11256,  -- Hmph!
        HERE_WE_GO_AGAIN                                                        = 11257,  -- Here we go again...
        I_HOPE_THAT_SHE_KNOWS_THAT_I_M                                          = 11258,  -- I hope that she knows that I'm only saying these things because I want to help her.
        YOU_SEE_WHEN_SHE_WAS_THIRTEEN_CHEMIOUE_LOST                             = 11259,  -- You see, when she was thirteen, Chemioue lost her older brother to an overgrown rose. Ever since then, she's turned to Justinius to fill the void in her heart left by her brother's death.
        CHEMIOUE_FEELS_ANGER_TOWARDS_PRISHE_ONLY_BECAUSE_SHE                    = 11260,  -- Chemioue feels anger towards Prishe only because she's trying to protect Justinius.
        I_JUST_WISH_THERE_WAS_SOMEONE_WHO_COULD                                 = 11261,  -- I just wish there was someone who could convince Chemioue of her faults before she does something drastic.
        IF_THAT_PARELBRIAUX_WERE_ONLY_A_LITTLE_MORE                             = 11262,  -- If that Parelbriaux were only a little more reliable...
        OH_PARELBRIAUX_WHY_DOES_TRESSIA_ALWAYS_HAVE_TO                          = 11263,  -- Oh, Parelbriaux! Why does Tressia always have to side with that wench!?
        CALM_DOWN_CHEMIOUE_WHILE_YOU_MAY_HAVE_YOUR                              = 11264,  -- Calm down, Chemioue. While you may have your differences, you should not speak that way of your friend.
        WHAT_IS_THIS_DO_NOT_TELL_ME_THAT                                        = 11265,  -- What is this? Do not tell me that you, too, have lost your mind.
        NO_I_WAS_JUST                                                           = 11266,  -- No, I was just...
        YOU_WERE_JUST_COME_ON_NOW_SPEAK_UP                                      = 11267,  -- You were just...? Come on now. Speak up!
        I_WAS_JUST_THINKING_THAT_MAYBE_YOU_RE                                   = 11268,  -- I was just thinking that maybe you're not giving Prishe a fair chance.
        A_FAIR_CHANCE_I                                                         = 11269,  -- A fair chance!? I--
        THERE_ARE_A_LOT_OF_PEOPLE_IN_THE                                        = 11270,  -- There are a lot of people in the safehold who look to Prishe for strength and guidance. What about those people?
        THOSE_PEOPLE                                                            = 11271,  -- Those people...
        SINCE_WHEN_DID_YOU_START_THINKING_ABOUT_ANYONE                          = 11272,  -- Since when did you start thinking about anyone other than your precious Ul--
        HM_DID_YOU_SAY_SOMETHING                                                = 11273,  -- Hm? Did you say something?
        NO_NO_TWAS_THE_WIND_MAYHAP                                              = 11274,  -- No, no. 'Twas the wind, mayhap...
        ANYWAY_YOU_D_FEEL_MUCH_BETTER_IF                                        = 11275,  -- Anyway, you'd feel much better if--
        I_TOLD_YOU_AS_LONG_AS_SHE_IS                                            = 11276,  -- I told you, as long as she is around, my heart and my mind shall never be at ease!
        SIGH_WELL_IF_THAT_IS_HOW_YOU_REALLY                                     = 11277,  -- <Sigh> Well, if that is how you really feel, why don't you tell her yourself? Or do you not have the confidence to face her?
        YOU_SHOULD_TALK_IF_ANYONE_LACKS_CONFIDENCE_TIS                          = 11278,  -- You should talk! If anyone lacks confidence, 'tis you!
        YES_MAYBE_IF_I_HAD_MORE_CONFIDENCE_I                                    = 11279,  -- ... Yes, maybe if I had more confidence, I could show everyone I'm more than just a doorboy...
        AND_MAYBE_I_COULD_TELL_HER_MY_TRUE                                      = 11280,  -- And maybe I could tell her my true feelings...
        NO_THAT_WOULD_NEVER_WORK                                                = 11281,  -- No. That would never work...
        WHAT_ABOUT_YOU_CHEMIOUE_WHAT_IF_YOU_COULD                               = 11282,  -- What about you, Chemioue? What if you could prove to everyone that you were just as strong and brave as Prishe?
        WHY_SHOULD_I_RISK_MY_LIFE_FOR_SOMETHING                                 = 11283,  -- Why should I risk my life for something as foolish as that?
        JUST_THINKING_OF_MYSELF_IN_THE_SAME_PRECARIOUS                          = 11284,  -- Just thinking of myself in the same precarious predicaments as Prishe makes me shudder.
        SHE_ALWAYS_BRAGS_THAT_HER_ENCOUNTERS_WERE_NOTHING                       = 11285,  -- She always brags that her encounters were nothing but danger that she must face...
        WAIT_A_MINUTE                                                           = 11286,  -- Wait a minute...
        COULD_THAT_BE_A_HINT_OF_WORRY_I                                         = 11287,  -- Could that be a hint of worry I sense?
