        THANK_YOU                                                               = 11376,  -- ... Thank you.
        DID_I_JUST_HEAR_WHAT_I_THINK_I                                          = 11377,  -- Did I just hear what I think I heard...?
        YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_WHAT_I_TOLD_CHEMIOUE                                   = 11378,  -- You wish to know what I told Chemioue before she left for the meadows?
        VERY_WELL_AS_YOU_MAY_ALREADY_KNOW_CHEMIOUE                              = 11379,  -- Very well. As you may already know, Chemioue's older brother was involved in a terrible accident that eventually claimed his life.
        WHAT_WAS_MOST_UNFORTUNATE_WAS_THAT_THE_WOUNDS                           = 11380,  -- What was most unfortunate was that the wounds her brother received were not incurable. However, there was no one in the safehold at the time that had the skills required to heal him.
        SINCE_THEN_THE_STUDY_OF_MEDICINE_HAS_BECOME                             = 11381,  -- Since then, the study of medicine has become Chemioue's passion. Perhaps she cannot live with the thought of someone else having to bear the same burden that she did.
        IN_ANY_CASE_THOSE_OF_US_WHO_KNOW                                        = 11382,  -- In any case, those of us who know her pain often treat her as if she were our little sister. And I feel that I might have, well...scolded her a little too hard.
        YOU_SEE_SHE_OFTEN_LOOKS_DOWN_UPON_ADVENTUROUS                           = 11383,  -- You see, she often looks down upon adventurous types such as yourself, probably because your lack of fear in the face of danger reminds Chemioue of a trait also found in her lost sibling.
        I_SIMPLY_TOLD_HER_THAT_WHILE_IT_MAY                                     = 11384,  -- I simply told her that while it may be difficult, she needs to open her heart and learn to accept people for who they are and what they do, and not necessarily the manner in which they do those things.
        I_APOLOGIZE_THAT_YOU_HAD_TO_BE_CAUGHT                                   = 11385,  -- I apologize that you had to be caught up in the petty affairs of our humble safehold. Please accept this as a token of our gratitude.
        YOUR_KINDNESS_MAY_HAVE_OPENED_A_DOOR_TO                                 = 11386,  -- Your kindness may have opened a door to a heart that has been locked up for far too long.
        I_HEAR_WORD_THAT_YOU_AIDED_JONETTE_IN                                   = 11387,  -- I hear word that you aided Jonette in her search for lost Tavnazian cuisine.
        SHE_WAS_SIMPLY_OVERJOYED_WITH_THE_RECIPES_YOU                           = 11388,  -- She was simply overjoyed with the recipes you brought her...
        I_WONDER_IF_I_MIGHT_ASK_YOU_A                                           = 11389,  -- I wonder if I might ask you a question...
        FROM_WHOM_DID_YOU_LEARN_OF_MY_PREVIOUS                                  = 11390,  -- From whom did you learn of my previous occupation as a merchant carrying goods between San d'Oria and Tavnazia?
        A_LADY_ROUVA_YOU_SAY_THAT_NAME_STIRS                                    = 11391,  -- A Lady Rouva, you say...? That name stirs the echo of a long-silent memory.
        IF_THIS_LADY_KNOWS_OF_MY_PAST_THEN                                      = 11392,  -- If this lady knows of my past, then perhaps she also remembers my dearly departed wife.
        WOULD_YOU_SPARE_A_MOMENT_TO_INDULGE_AN                                  = 11393,  -- Would you spare a moment to indulge an old man's sentimentality...?
        THIS_BELONGED_TO_MY_WIFE                                                = 11394,  -- This belonged to my wife.
        I_KNOW_NOT_WHERE_OR_WHENCE_IT_WAS                                       = 11395,  -- I know not where or whence it was crafted...
        MY_WIFE_PRIZED_THIS_POSSESSION_ABOVE_ALL_OTHERS                         = 11396,  -- My wife prized this possession above all others, but never had the chance to speak of its origin before she...
        IF_YOU_HAVE_THE_OPPORTUNITY_TO_VISIT_THE                                = 11397,  -- If you have the opportunity to visit the city of San d'Oria, mayhap you could ask Lady Rouva of its significance? May Altana keep you safe on your travels, %.
        YOU_HAVE_DISCOVERED_THE_ORIGIN_OF_MY_WIFE                               = 11398,  -- You have discovered the origin of my wife's %? And I see you have gone to the trouble of restoring its sheen, as well.
        THERE_IS_AN_INSCRIPTION_ON_THE_YOU_SAY                                  = 11399,  -- There is an inscription on the %, you say?
        LET_ME_SEE_HERE_REGRETS_WILT_NOT_PLAGUE                                 = 11400,  -- Let me see here... Regrets wilt not plague...
        WOULD_YOU_CARE_TO_LISTEN_TO_A_STORY                                     = 11401,  -- %... Would you care to listen to a story?
        OUR_ONLY_DAUGHTER_ULMIA_S_MOTHER_WAS_A                                  = 11402,  -- Our only daughter, Ulmia's mother, was a deeply pious child.
        PERHAPS_IT_WAS_THE_INFLUENCE_OF_MY_WIFE                                 = 11403,  -- Perhaps it was the influence of my wife with her upbringing in the San d'Orian Cathedral.
        IN_THOSE_DAYS_I_WAS_ASSAILED_BY_COMPLICATED                             = 11404,  -- In those days I was assailed by complicated feelings every time my wife and daughter would speak of the Goddess...
        FEELINGS_OF_ESTRANGEMENT_AND_GUILT_SO_MANY_UNRULY                       = 11405,  -- Feelings of estrangement and guilt... So many unruly emotions surged within me. After all, I was but a simple merchant with no great understanding of philosophy or religion.
        I_FELT_I_HAD_STOLEN_MY_WIFE_AWAY                                        = 11406,  -- I felt I had stolen my wife away from her faith. Did she ever regret her decision to marry me?
        EVEN_AFTER_MY_WIFE_LEFT_THIS_WORLD_AND                                  = 11407,  -- Even after my wife left this world, and later when Ulmia's parents joined her in Paradise, these doubts continued to gnaw at my soul.
        ULMIA_GREATLY_RESEMBLES_HER_MOTHER_AND_GRANDMOTHER_IN                   = 11408,  -- Ulmia greatly resembles her mother and grandmother in many respects. I see the same features, the same faith, the same talent...
        WHEN_ULMIA_DECLARED_SHE_WOULD_ONCE_AGAIN_LEAVE                          = 11409,  -- When Ulmia declared she would once again leave the safehold, I thought my heart would burst with apprehension.
        I_ENTERTAINED_THE_THOUGHT_THAT_ALTANA_HAD_COME                          = 11410,  -- I entertained the thought that Altana had come to claim my granddaughter as well...
        BUT_I_BELIEVE_THAT_ULMIA_HOLDS_TO_HER                                   = 11411,  -- But I believe that Ulmia holds to her own type of faith.
        AND_THAT_MY_WIFE_HELD_NO_REGRETS                                        = 11412,  -- And that my wife held no regrets...
        MORE_THAN_ANYTHING_I_WISH_TO_KEEP_MY                                    = 11413,  -- More than anything, I wish to keep my faith in that belief.
        NO_REGRETS                                                              = 11414,  -- No regrets...
        THANK_YOU_FOR_LISTENING_SO_LONG_TO_MY                                   = 11415,  -- Thank you for listening so long to my ramblings.
        PLEASE_ACCEPT_THIS_FOR_PUTTING_A_GRANDFATHER_S                          = 11416,  -- Please accept this for putting a grandfather's heart at ease.
        WHY_YOU_DON_T_LOOK_LIKE_YOU_ARE                                         = 11417,  -- Why, you don't look like you are a native to the archipelago. Are you trapped here as well?
        I_TRAVELED_TO_JEUNO_FROM_MY_HOME_COUNTRY                                = 11418,  -- I traveled to Jeuno from my home country in the Near East to continue my research in various types of matter and antimatter. However, one day while I was collecting specimens in the caves around Delkfutt's Tower, I fell into some strange vortex. When I woke up, I found myself here on this island with no way to return home.
        HOW_AM_I_SUPPOSED_TO_CONTINUE_MY_STUDIES                                = 11419,  -- How am I supposed to continue my studies in such an inconvenient location!?
        HMMM_THE_REVERSE_FLUCTUATION_OF_ALPHA_THERMO_WAVES                      = 11420,  -- Hmmm... The reverse fluctuation of alpha-thermo waves can be considered a sign of protomutation...
        BUT_THE_RESULTING_FLOW_OF_EXOPARTICLES_THAT_ACCOMPANIES                 = 11421,  -- But the resulting flow of exoparticles that accompanies the hyporeaction drastically hinders the growth of new biomatter...
        H_HOW_DARE_YOU_SNEAK_UP_ON_A                                            = 11422,  -- H-how dare you sneak up on a lady like that! Leave now before I call the Tavnazian Patrol!
        HM_YOU_WOULD_LIKE_TO_KNOW_WHAT_I                                        = 11423,  -- Hm? You would like to know what I'm doing? It's fairly complicated, and you look awfully busy...
        HM_YOU_WOULD_LIKE_TO_KNOW_WHAT_I_2                                      = 11424,  -- Hm? You would like to know what I'm doing? I don't know... You probably won't find it very interesting...
        HM_YOU_WOULD_LIKE_TO_KNOW_WHAT_I_3                                      = 11425,  -- Hm? You would like to know what I'm doing? I don't think it concerns you, but...
        WELL_HURRY_UP_AND_TELL_ME_IF_YOU                                        = 11426,  -- Well...? Hurry up and tell me! If you put it that way.
        ALRIGHT_RECENTLY_I_VE_BEGUN_RESEARCH_ON_NEW                             = 11427,  -- Alright... Recently I've begun research on new methods of matter processing. If I succeed, my theories could rival the primitive methods of conventional synthesis.
        VERY_GOOD_NOW_BE_ON_YOUR_WAY_SO                                         = 11428,  -- Very good. Now be on your way so I can return to my studies.
        YOU_SEE_IN_ADDITION_TO_CRYSTALS_THERE_ARE                               = 11429,  -- You see, in addition to crystals, there are certain unique types of matter that, when used as a catalyst, can transmogrify normal, everyday items into creations never seen before by man or woman! I like to call that substance Xenomatter.
        I_M_STILL_IN_THE_BEGINNING_STAGES_OF                                    = 11430,  -- I'm still in the beginning stages of my research, but I've already discovered a way to manipulate Xenomatter in a way that it can be used to multiply the strength and durability of certain materials. I hope that my further studies will result in the discovery of even more benefits.
        LET_ME_EXPLAIN_FURTHER_FOR_EXAMPLE_SAY_I                                = 11431,  -- Let me explain further... For example, say I was to attempt to alter the polymolecular makeup of this clam using the Xenomatter in question. As you know, this particular variety of clam only lives in the shallows of a certain tiny island far off the coast of southeastern Mindartia.
        TO_FIND_ONE_OF_THESE_SPECIMENS_NOT_ONLY                                 = 11432,  -- To find one of these specimens, not only would one have to be an expert on the clam's native habitat, but also be knowledgeable of their mating and feeding patterns, their reactions to the rise and fall of geothermal temperature levels, as well as their migratory tendencies, and how all these are affected by the varying seasonal lunar cycles. In other words, it is extremely difficult.
        HOWEVER_LARGE_QUANTITIES_OF_THIS_RARE_SPECIES_OF                        = 11433,  -- However, large quantities of this rare species of bivalve mollusk are crucial in order to procure enough reliable data to prove my hypotheses infallible. Unfortunately, due to the difficulty in acquiring the specimens, I often find myself in quite a predicament. A single experiment consists of placing three medium-sized clams in a hypophosphorous chamber laced with a small quantity of Xenomatter.
        AFTER_SEALING_THE_BOX_WITH_A_CERMOPOLYMER_COMPOUND                      = 11434,  -- After sealing the box with a cermopolymer compound (to prevent unnecessary carbo-oxidization), it is only a matter of minutes before a micronucleic reaction occurs and a minute quantity of fluoroplasm is released.
        I_HAVE_COME_TO_THE_CONCLUSION_THAT_THE                                  = 11435,  -- I have come to the conclusion that the energy for this reaction comes from the calcitron particles concealed within the mucocide membranes located between the abdominal region of the clam and its shell. Unfortunately, during the plasmatic release of free radicals, the specimen experiences a rapid loss of aminofluids and eventually turns to ash, therefore preventing me from using the same clam in a future test.
        OVERALL_WHILE_I_REALIZE_THAT_THE_IMPACT_THE                             = 11436,  -- Overall, while I realize that the impact the excessive gathering of new specimens may have on the island's aquaculture could be catastrophic, I am ultimately left with no other option. Who am I to turn my back on scientific progress?
        NOW_AS_I_WAS_SAYING_WHEN_APPLIED_TO                                     = 11437,  -- Now as I was saying, when applied to the clams, the Xenomatter causes a photomutegenic reaction that eventually reduces the specimen to a pile of neutrinogen-rich ashes (those ashes tend to be alkaline-based; however, I have yet to determine the significance of this phenomenon).
        IF_I_CAN_FIND_THE_REASON_BEHIND_THE                                     = 11438,  -- If I can find the reason behind the aminofluid loss and its relation with the plasmatic release, I may be able to explain the finite relation of the clams' hydroplasma-oriented biomorphic structure to the quasizymotic nature of Xenomatter. And if I succeed in that, it won't be long before I am...
        OW_I_BIT_MY_THONGUE_UM_WON_T                                            = 11439,  -- Ow! I bit my thongue... Um... Won't the long thefore I...I...uthe that data to therfect a new nethod of natter throthething. ......... ...... ...
